(2264, 2264, 'Ἡρώδης', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"heroic\",\"short\":\"heroic; Herod, the name of four Jewish kings\",\"long\":[\"the name of a royal family that flourished among the Jews in the times of Christ and the Apostles\",[\"Herod the Great (the ruler of Judaea when Jesus Christ was born\",\"Herod surnamed \\\"Antipas,\\\" the son of Herod the Great, (the ruler during the latter part of Jesus\' earthly life\",\"Herod Agrippa I, the son of Aristobulus and Berenice and grandson of Herod the Great, (he ordered James to be executed and imprisoned Peter)\",\"Herod Agrippa II (referred to in the New Testament simply as Agrippa), son of Herod Agrippa I (he was almost persuaded to become a Christian by Paul\'s arguments)\"]]},\"deriv\":\"compound of ἥρως (a \\\"hero\\\") and G1491\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"heˈro.ðes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞ˈrow.ðe̞s\",\"sbl\":\"hērōdēs\",\"dic\":\"hay-ROH-thase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-ROH-thase\"},\"see\":[\"G1491\"],\"comment\":\"Herod the Great was the son of Antipater of Idumaea. Appointed king of Judaea 40 BC by the Roman Senate at the suggestion of Antony and with the consent of Octavian, he at length overcame the great opposition which the country made to him and took possession of the kingdom 37 BC; and after the battle of Actium, he was confirmed by Octavian, whose favor he ever enjoyed. He was brave and skilled in war, learned and sagacious; but also extremely suspicious and cruel. Hence he destroyed the entire royal family of Hasmonaeans, put to death many of the Jews that opposed his government, and proceeded to kill even his dearly beloved wife Mariamne of the Hasmonaean line and his two sons she had borne him. By these acts of bloodshed, and especially by his love and imitation of Roman customs and institutions and by the burdensome taxes imposed upon his subjects, he so alienated the Jews that he was unable to regain their favor by his splendid restoration of the temple and other acts of munificence. He died at the age of 70 in the 37th year of his reign, the 4th before the Dionysian era. In his closing years, John the Baptist and Christ were born; Matthew narrates that he commanded all the male children under two years old in Bethlehem to be slain. Herod Antipas was the son of Herod the Great and Malthace, a Samaritan woman. After the death of his father he was appointed by the Romans tetrarch of Galilee and Peraea. His first wife was the daughter of Aretas, king of Arabia; but he subsequently repudiated her and took to himself Herodias, the wife of his brother Herod Philip; and in consequence Aretas, his father-in-law, made war against him and conquered him. He cast John the Baptist into prison because John had rebuked him for this unlawful connection; and afterwards, at the instigation of Herodias, he ordered him to be beheaded. Induced by her, too, he went to Rome to obtain from the emperor the title of king. But in consequence of the accusations brought against him by Herod Agrippa I, Caligula banished him (AD 39) to Lugdunum in Gaul, where he seems to have died. He was light minded, sensual and vicious. Herod Agrippa I was the son of Aristobulus and Berenice, and grandson of Herod the Great. After various changes in fortune, he gained the favor of Caligula and Claudius to such a degree that he gradually obtained the government of all of Palestine, with the title of king. He died at Caesarea, AD 44, at the age of 54, in the seventh (or the 4th, reckoning from the extension of his dominions by Claudius) year of his reign, just after having ordered James the apostle, son of Zebedee, to be slain, and Peter to be cast into prison (see Acts 12:21) (Herod) Agrippa II, son of Herod Agrippa I. When his father died he was a youth of seventeen. In AD 48 he received from Claudius Caesar the government of Chalcis, with the right of appointing the Jewish high priests, together with the care and oversight of the temple at Jerusalem. Four years later Claudius took from him Chalcis and gave him instead a larger domain, of Batanaea, Trachonitis, and Gaulanitis, with the title of king. To those reigns Nero, in AD 53, added Tiberias and Taricheae and Peraean Julias, with fourteen neighbouring villages. He is mentioned in Acts 25 and 26. In the Jewish war, although he strove in vain to restrain the fury of the seditious and bellicose populace, he did not desert to the Roman side. After the fall of Jerusalem, he was vested with praetorian rank and kept the kingdom entire until his death, which took place in the third year of the emperor Trajan, (the 73rd year of his life, and the 52nd of his reign). He was the last representative of the Herodian dynasty.\"}', 'Herod'),
(2265, 2265, 'Ἡρωδιανοί', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"Herodians, i.e., partisans of Herod\",\"long\":[\"Herodians, i.e., Herod\'s partisans, Herod\'s supporters\"]},\"deriv\":\"plural of a derivative of G2264\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"he.ro.ði.ɑˈny\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞.row.ði.ɑˈny\",\"sbl\":\"hērōdianoi\",\"dic\":\"hay-roh-thee-ah-NOO\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-roh-thee-ah-NOO\"},\"see\":[\"G2264\"]}', 'Herodians'),
(2266, 2266, 'Ἡρωδιάς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"heroic\",\"short\":\"Herodias, a woman of the Heodian family\",\"long\":[\"daughter of Aristobulus and granddaughter of Herod the Great\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2264\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"he.ro.ðiˈɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞.row.ðiˈɑs\",\"sbl\":\"hērōdias\",\"dic\":\"hay-roh-thee-AS\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-roh-thee-AS\"},\"see\":[\"G2264\"],\"comment\":\"She was first married to Herod Philip I, son of Herod the Great, but afterwards formed an unlawful union with Herod Antipas, whom she induced not only to slay John the Baptist but also to make the journey to Rome which ruined him. In the end, she followed him to exile in Gaul.\"}', 'Herodias'),
(2267, 2267, 'Ἡρωδίων', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"heroic\",\"short\":\"Herodion, a Christian\",\"long\":[\"a certain Christian\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2264\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"he.roˈði.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞.rowˈði.own\",\"sbl\":\"hērōdiōn\",\"dic\":\"hay-roh-THEE-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-roh-THEE-one\"},\"see\":[\"G2264\"]}', 'Herodion'),
(2268, 2268, 'Ἡσαΐας', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"Jehovah\'s help\",\"short\":\"Hesaias (i.e., Jeshajah), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"a famous Hebrew prophet who prophesied in the reigns of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3470)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"he.sɑˈi.ɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞.sɑˈi.ɑs\",\"sbl\":\"hēsaias\",\"dic\":\"hay-sa-EE-as\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-sa-EE-as\"},\"see\":[\"H3470\"]}', 'Esaias'),
(2269, 2269, 'Ἠσαῦ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"hairy\",\"short\":\"Esau, an Edomite\",\"long\":[\"was the eldest son of Isaac and twin brother of Jacob\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H6215)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"eˈsɑβ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞ˈsɑf\",\"sbl\":\"ēsau\",\"dic\":\"ay-SAV\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-SAF\"},\"see\":[\"H6215\"]}', 'Esau'),
(2270, 2270, 'ἡσυχάζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to keep still (intransitively), i.e., refrain from labor, meddlesomeness or speech\",\"long\":[\"to keep quiet\",[\"to rest, cease from labor\",\"to lead a quiet life, said of those who are not running hither and thither, but stay at home and mind their business\",\"to be silent, i.e., to say nothing, hold one\'s peace\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from the same as G2272\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"he.syˈxɑ.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞.sjuˈxɑ.zow\",\"sbl\":\"hēsychazō\",\"dic\":\"hay-soo-HA-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-syoo-HA-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2272\"]}', 'cease, hold peace, be quiet, rest'),
(2271, 2271, 'ἡσυχία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"(as noun) stillness, i.e., desistance from bustle or language\",\"long\":[\"quietness\",[\"description of the life of one who stays at home doing his own work, and does not officiously meddle with the affairs of others\"],\"silence\"]},\"deriv\":\"feminine of G2272\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"he.syˈxi.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞.sjuˈxi.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"hēsychia\",\"dic\":\"hay-soo-HEE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-syoo-HEE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2272\"]}', 'quietness, silence'),
(2272, 2272, 'ἡσύχιος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"properly, keeping one\'s seat (sedentary), i.e., (by implication) still (undisturbed, undisturbing)\",\"long\":[\"quiet, tranquil\"]},\"deriv\":\"a prolonged form of a compound probably of a derivative of the base of G1476 and perhaps G2192\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"heˈsy.xi.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞ˈsju.çi.ows\",\"sbl\":\"hēsychios\",\"dic\":\"hay-SOO-hee-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-SYOO-hee-ose\"},\"see\":[\"G1476\",\"G2192\"]}', 'peaceable, quiet'),
(2273, 2273, 'ἤτοι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"either indeed\",\"long\":[\"whether, either\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2228 and G5104\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈe.ty\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈe̞.ty\",\"sbl\":\"ētoi\",\"dic\":\"A-too\",\"dic_mod\":\"A-too\"},\"see\":[\"G2228\",\"G5104\"]}', 'whether'),
(2274, 2274, 'ἡττάω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to make worse, i.e., vanquish (literally or figuratively); by implication, to rate lower\",\"long\":[\"to make less, inferior, to overcome\",[\"to be made inferior\",\"to overcome, worsted, to be conquered by one, forced to yield to one\",\"to hold a thing inferior, set below\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from the same as G2276\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hetˈtɑ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞tˈtɑ.ow\",\"sbl\":\"hēttaō\",\"dic\":\"hate-TA-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ate-TA-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2276\"]}', 'be inferior, overcome'),
(2275, 2275, 'ἥττημα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a deterioration, i.e., (objectively) failure or (subjectively) loss\",\"long\":[\"a diminution, decrease: i.e., defeat\",\"loss, as respects to salvation\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2274\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈhet.te.mɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈe̞t.te̞.mɑ\",\"sbl\":\"hēttēma\",\"dic\":\"HATE-tay-ma\",\"dic_mod\":\"ATE-tay-ma\"},\"see\":[\"G2274\"]}', 'diminishing, fault'),
(2276, 2276, 'ἥττον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"worse (as noun); by implication, less (as adverb)\",\"long\":[\"inferior\",\"less\"]},\"deriv\":\"neuter of comparative of ἧκα (slightly) used for that of G2556\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈhet.ton\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈe̞t.town\",\"sbl\":\"hētton\",\"dic\":\"HATE-tone\",\"dic_mod\":\"ATE-tone\"},\"see\":[\"G2556\"]}', 'less, worse'),
(2277, 2277, 'ἤτω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"let him (or it) be\",\"long\":[\"let him (it) be\"]},\"deriv\":\"third person singular imperative of G1510\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈe.to\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈe̞.tow\",\"sbl\":\"ētō\",\"dic\":\"A-toh\",\"dic_mod\":\"A-toh\"},\"see\":[\"G1510\"]}', 'let...be'),
(2278, 2278, 'ἠχέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to make a loud noise, i.e., reverberate\",\"long\":[\"to sound\",[\"used of the roaring of the sea\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2279\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"eˈxɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"e̞ˈxe̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"ēcheō\",\"dic\":\"ay-HEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ay-HAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2279\"]}', 'roar, sound'),
(2279, 2279, 'ἦχος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a loud or confused noise (\\\"echo\\\"), i.e., roar; figuratively, a rumor\",\"long\":[\"a sound, noise\",[\"spoken of the roar of the sea waves\"],\"rumour, report\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈe.xos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈe̞.xows\",\"sbl\":\"ēchos\",\"dic\":\"A-hose\",\"dic_mod\":\"A-hose\"}}', 'fame, sound'),
(2280, 2280, 'Θαδδαῖος', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"large hearted, courageous\",\"short\":\"Thaddaeus, one of the Apostles\",\"long\":[\"one of the twelve apostles, also apparently known as Lebbaeus, Judas, and Jude\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɑðˈðɛ.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θɑðˈðe.ows\",\"sbl\":\"thaddaios\",\"dic\":\"thahth-THEH-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"thahth-THAY-ose\"},\"comment\":\"From a comparison with the list of apostles in Luke 6:16 and Acts 1:13, it seems that Judas, Lebbaeus and Thaddaeus were the same person and the writer of the book of Jude.\"}', 'Thaddaeus'),
(2281, 2281, 'θάλασσα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"the sea (genitive case or specially)\",\"long\":[\"the sea\",[\"used of the sea in general\",\"used specifically of the Mediterranean Sea or the Red Sea\"]]},\"deriv\":\"probably prolonged from G0251\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɑ.lɑs.sɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθɑ.lɑs.sɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thalassa\",\"dic\":\"THA-lahs-sa\",\"dic_mod\":\"THA-lahs-sa\"},\"see\":[\"G0251\"]}', 'sea'),
(2282, 2282, 'θάλπω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to brood, i.e., (figuratively) to foster\",\"long\":[\"to warm, keep warm\",\"to cherish with tender love, to foster with tender care\"]},\"deriv\":\"probably akin to θάλλω (to warm)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɑl.po\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθɑl.pow\",\"sbl\":\"thalpō\",\"dic\":\"THAHL-poh\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAHL-poh\"}}', 'cherish'),
(2283, 2283, 'Θάμαρ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"palm tree\",\"short\":\"Thamar (i.e., Tamar), an Israelitess\",\"long\":[\"Thamar (or Tamar), the wife of the two sons of Judah, Er and Onan\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H8559)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɑ.mɑr\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθɑ.mɑr\",\"sbl\":\"thamar\",\"dic\":\"THA-mahr\",\"dic_mod\":\"THA-mahr\"},\"see\":[\"H8559\"]}', 'Thamar'),
(2284, 2284, 'θαμβέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to stupefy (with surprise), i.e., astound\",\"long\":[\"to be astonished\",\"to astonish, terrify\",[\"to be amazed\",\"to be frightened\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2285\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɑmˈβɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θɑɱˈve̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thambeō\",\"dic\":\"thahm-VEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thahm-VAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2285\"]}', 'amaze, astonish'),
(2285, 2285, 'θάμβος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"stupefaction (by surprise), i.e., astonishment\",\"long\":[\"to render immovable\",\"amazement\"]},\"deriv\":\"akin to an obsolete τάφω (to dumbfound)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɑm.βos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθɑɱ.vows\",\"sbl\":\"thambos\",\"dic\":\"THAHM-vose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAHM-vose\"}}', 'X amazed, + astonished, wonder'),
(2286, 2286, 'θανάσιμος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"fatal, i.e., poisonous\",\"long\":[\"deadly\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2288\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɑˈnɑ.si.mos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θɑˈnɑ.si.mows\",\"sbl\":\"thanasimos\",\"dic\":\"tha-NA-see-mose\",\"dic_mod\":\"tha-NA-see-mose\"},\"see\":[\"G2288\"]}', 'deadly'),
(2287, 2287, 'θανατήφορος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"death-bearing, i.e., fatal\",\"long\":[\"death bringing, deadly\"]},\"deriv\":\"from (the feminine form of) G2288 and G5342\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɑ.nɑˈte.fo.ros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θɑ.nɑˈte̞.fow.rows\",\"sbl\":\"thanatēphoros\",\"dic\":\"tha-na-TAY-foh-rose\",\"dic_mod\":\"tha-na-TAY-foh-rose\"},\"see\":[\"G2288\",\"G5342\"]}', 'deadly'),
(2288, 2288, 'θάνατος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"(properly, an adjective used as a noun) death (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"the death of the body\",[\"that separation (whether natural or violent) of the soul and the body by which the life on earth is ended\",\"with the implied idea of future misery in hell\",[\"the power of death\"],\"since the nether world, the abode of the dead, was conceived as being very dark, it is equivalent to the region of thickest darkness i.e., figuratively, a region enveloped in the darkness of ignorance and sin\"],\"metaphorically, the loss of that life which alone is worthy of the name,\",[\"the misery of the soul arising from sin, which begins on earth but lasts and increases after the death of the body in hell\"],\"the miserable state of the wicked dead in hell\",\"in the widest sense, death comprising all the miseries arising from sin, as well physical death as the loss of a life consecrated to God and blessed in him on earth, to be followed by wretchedness in hell\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2348\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɑ.nɑ.tos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθɑ.nɑ.tows\",\"sbl\":\"thanatos\",\"dic\":\"THA-na-tose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THA-na-tose\"},\"see\":[\"G2348\"]}', 'X deadly, (be...) death'),
(2289, 2289, 'θανατόω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to kill\",\"long\":[\"to put to death\",\"metaphorically\",[\"to make to die i.e., destroy, render extinct\",\"by death to be liberated from the bond of anything, literally to be made dead in relation to (something)\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2288 to kill (literally or figuratively)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɑ.nɑˈto.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θɑ.nɑˈtow.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thanatoō\",\"dic\":\"tha-na-TOH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"tha-na-TOH-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2288\"]}', 'become dead, (cause to be) put to death, kill, mortify'),
(2290, 2290, 'θάπτω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to celebrate funeral rites, i.e., inter\",\"long\":[\"to bury, inter\"]},\"deriv\":\"a primary verb\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɑ.pto\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθɑ.ptow\",\"sbl\":\"thaptō\",\"dic\":\"THA-ptoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"THA-ptoh\"}}', 'bury'),
(2291, 2291, 'Θάρα', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"station\",\"short\":\"Thara (i.e., Terach), the father of Abraham\",\"long\":[\"the father of Abraham\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H8646)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɑ.rɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθɑ.rɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thara\",\"dic\":\"THA-ra\",\"dic_mod\":\"THA-ra\"},\"see\":[\"H8646\"]}', 'Thara'),
(2292, 2292, 'θαῤῥέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to exercise courage\",\"long\":[\"to be of good courage, be of good cheer\",\"to be bold\"]},\"deriv\":\"another form for G2293\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɑrˈrɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θɑrˈre̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"tharrheō\",\"dic\":\"thahr-REH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thahr-RAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2293\",\"G5111\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G5111.\"}', 'be bold, X boldly, have confidence, be confident'),
(2293, 2293, 'θαρσέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to have courage\",\"long\":[\"to be of good courage, be of good cheer\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2294\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɑrˈsɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θɑrˈse̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"tharseō\",\"dic\":\"thahr-SEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thahr-SAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2292\",\"G2294\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G2292.\"}', 'be of good cheer (comfort)'),
(2294, 2294, 'θάρσος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"boldness (subjectively)\",\"long\":[\"courage, confidence\"]},\"deriv\":\"akin (by transposition) to θράσος (daring)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɑr.sos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθɑr.sows\",\"sbl\":\"tharsos\",\"dic\":\"THAHR-sose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAHR-sose\"}}', 'courage'),
(2295, 2295, 'θαῦμα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"wonder (properly concrete; but by implication, abstract)\",\"long\":[\"a wonderful thing, a marvel\",\"wonder\",[\"to wonder [with great wonder i.e.,] exceedingly\"]]},\"deriv\":\"apparently from a form of G2300\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɛβ.mɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθa.mɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thauma\",\"dic\":\"THEV-ma\",\"dic_mod\":\"THA-ma\"},\"see\":[\"G2300\"]}', 'admiration'),
(2296, 2296, 'θαυμάζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to wonder; by implication, to admire\",\"long\":[\"to wonder, wonder at, marvel\",\"to be wondered at, to be had in admiration\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2295\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛβˈmɑ.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θaˈmɑ.zow\",\"sbl\":\"thaumazō\",\"dic\":\"thev-MA-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"tha-MA-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2295\"]}', 'admire, have in admiration, marvel, wonder'),
(2297, 2297, 'θαυμάσιος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"wondrous, i.e., (neuter as noun) a miracle\",\"long\":[\"wonderful, marvellous\",\"wonderful deeds, wonders\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2295\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛβˈmɑ.si.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θaˈmɑ.si.ows\",\"sbl\":\"thaumasios\",\"dic\":\"thev-MA-see-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"tha-MA-see-ose\"},\"see\":[\"G2295\"]}', 'wonderful thing'),
(2298, 2298, 'θαυμαστός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"wondered at, i.e., (by implication) wonderful\",\"long\":[\"wonderful, marvellous\",[\"worthy of pious admiration, admirable, excellent\",\"passing human comprehension\",\"causing amazement joined with terror\",\"marvellous\",[\"extraordinary, striking, surprising\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2296\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛβ.mɑˈstos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θa.mɑˈstows\",\"sbl\":\"thaumastos\",\"dic\":\"thev-ma-STOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"tha-ma-STOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2296\"]}', 'marvel(-lous)'),
(2299, 2299, 'θεά', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a female deity\",\"long\":[\"a goddess\"]},\"deriv\":\"feminine of G2316\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thea\",\"dic\":\"theh-AH\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-AH\"},\"see\":[\"G2316\"]}', 'goddess'),
(2300, 2300, 'θεάομαι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to look closely at, i.e., (by implication) perceive (literally or figuratively); by extension to visit\",\"long\":[\"to behold, look upon, view attentively, contemplate (often used of public shows)\",[\"of important persons that are looked on with admiration\"],\"to view, take a view of\",[\"in the sense of visiting, meeting with a person\"],\"to learn by looking, to see with the eyes, to perceive\"]},\"deriv\":\"a prolonged form of a primary verb\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈɑ.o.mɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈɑ.ow.me\",\"sbl\":\"theaomai\",\"dic\":\"theh-AH-oh-meh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-AH-oh-may\"},\"see\":[\"G3700\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G3700.\"}', 'behold, look (upon), see'),
(2301, 2301, 'θεατρίζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to expose as a spectacle\",\"long\":[\"to bring upon the stage\",\"to set forth as a spectacle, expose to contempt\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2302\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.ɑˈtri.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.ɑˈtri.zow\",\"sbl\":\"theatrizō\",\"dic\":\"theh-ah-TREE-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ah-TREE-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2302\"]}', 'make a gazing stock'),
(2302, 2302, 'θέατρον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a place for public show (\\\"theatre\\\"), i.e., general audience-room; by implication, a show itself (figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"a theatre, a place in which games and dramatic spectacles are exhibited, and public assemblies held (for the Greeks used the theatre also as a forum)\",\"a public show\",[\"metaphorically, a man who is exhibited to be gazed at and made sport of\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2300\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɛ.ɑ.tron\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞.ɑ.trown\",\"sbl\":\"theatron\",\"dic\":\"THEH-ah-trone\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAY-ah-trone\"},\"see\":[\"G2300\"]}', 'spectacle, theatre'),
(2303, 2303, 'θεῖον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"sulphur\",\"long\":[\"brimstone\",[\"divine incense, because burning brimstone was regarded as having power to purify, and to ward off disease\"]]},\"deriv\":\"probably neuter of G2304 (in its original sense of flashing)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθi.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθi.own\",\"sbl\":\"theion\",\"dic\":\"THEE-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"THEE-one\"},\"see\":[\"G2304\"]}', 'brimstone'),
(2304, 2304, 'θεῖος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"godlike (neuter as noun, divinity)\",\"long\":[\"a general name of deities or divinities as used by the Greeks\",\"spoken of the only and true God, trinity\",[\"of Christ\",\"Holy Spirit\",\"the Father\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2316\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθi.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθi.ows\",\"sbl\":\"theios\",\"dic\":\"THEE-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THEE-ose\"},\"see\":[\"G2316\"]}', 'divine, godhead'),
(2305, 2305, 'θειότης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"divinity (abstractly)\",\"long\":[\"divinity, divine nature\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2304\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θiˈo.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θiˈow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"theiotēs\",\"dic\":\"thee-OH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"thee-OH-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2304\"]}', 'godhead'),
(2306, 2306, 'θειώδης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"sulphur-like, i.e., sulphurous\",\"long\":[\"of brimstone, sulphurous\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2303 and 1491\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θiˈo.ðes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θiˈow.ðe̞s\",\"sbl\":\"theiōdēs\",\"dic\":\"thee-OH-thase\",\"dic_mod\":\"thee-OH-thase\"},\"see\":[\"G2303\"]}', 'brimstone'),
(2307, 2307, 'θέλημα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a determination (properly, the thing), i.e., (actively) choice (specially, purpose, decree; abstractly, volition) or (passively) inclination\",\"long\":[\"what one wishes or has determined shall be done\",[\"of the purpose of God to bless mankind through Christ\",\"of what God wishes to be done by us\",[\"commands, precepts\"]],\"will, choice, inclination, desire, pleasure\"]},\"deriv\":\"from the prolonged form of G2309\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɛ.le.mɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞.le̞.mɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thelēma\",\"dic\":\"THEH-lay-ma\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAY-lay-ma\"},\"see\":[\"G2309\"]}', 'desire, pleasure, will'),
(2308, 2308, 'θέλησις', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"determination (properly, the act), i.e., option\",\"long\":[\"a willing will\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2309\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɛ.le.sis\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞.le̞.sis\",\"sbl\":\"thelēsis\",\"dic\":\"THEH-lay-sees\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAY-lay-sees\"},\"see\":[\"G2309\"]}', 'will'),
(2309, 2309, 'θέλω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to determine (as an active option from subjective impulse; whereas G1014 properly denotes rather a passive acquiescence in objective considerations), i.e., choose or prefer (literally or figuratively); by implication, to wish, i.e., be inclined to (sometimes adverbially, gladly); impersonally for the future tense, to be about to; by Hebraism, to delight in\",\"long\":[\"to will, have in mind, intend\",[\"to be resolved or determined, to purpose\",\"to desire, to wish\",\"to love\",[\"to like to do a thing, be fond of doing\"],\"to take delight in, have pleasure\"]]},\"deriv\":\"apparently strengthened from the alternate form of G0138\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɛ.lo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞.low\",\"sbl\":\"thelō\",\"dic\":\"THEH-loh\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAY-loh\"},\"see\":[\"G0138\",\"G1014\"]}', 'desire, be disposed (forward), intend, list, love, mean, please, have rather, (be) will(-ing(-ly)) (have)'),
(2310, 2310, 'θεμέλιος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"something put down, i.e., a substruction (of a building, etc.), (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"laid down as a foundation, the foundation (of a building, wall, city)\",\"metaphorically the foundations, beginnings, first principals\",[\"of institution or system of truth\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of G5087\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈmɛ.li.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈme̞.li.ows\",\"sbl\":\"themelios\",\"dic\":\"theh-MEH-lee-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-MAY-lee-ose\"},\"see\":[\"G5087\"]}', 'foundation'),
(2311, 2311, 'θεμελιόω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to lay a basis for, i.e., (literally) erect, or (figuratively) consolidate\",\"long\":[\"to lay the foundation, to found\",\"to make stable, establish\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2310\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.mɛ.liˈo.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.me̞.liˈow.ow\",\"sbl\":\"themelioō\",\"dic\":\"theh-meh-lee-OH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-may-lee-OH-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2310\"]}', '(lay the) found(-ation), ground, settle'),
(2312, 2312, 'θεοδίδακτος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"divinely instructed\",\"long\":[\"taught of God\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2316 and G1321\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.oˈði.ðɑk.tos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.owˈði.ðɑk.tows\",\"sbl\":\"theodidaktos\",\"dic\":\"theh-oh-THEE-thahk-tose\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-oh-THEE-thahk-tose\"},\"see\":[\"G1321\",\"G2316\"]}', 'taught of God'),
(2313, 2313, 'θεομαχέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to resist deity\",\"long\":[\"to fight against God\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2314\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.o.mɑˈxɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.ow.mɑˈxe̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"theomacheō\",\"dic\":\"theh-oh-ma-HEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-oh-ma-HAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2314\"]}', 'fight against God'),
(2314, 2314, 'θεομάχος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"an opponent of deity\",\"long\":[\"fighting against God, resisting God\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2316 and G3164\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.oˈmɑ.xos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.owˈmɑ.xows\",\"sbl\":\"theomachos\",\"dic\":\"theh-oh-MA-hose\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-oh-MA-hose\"},\"see\":[\"G2316\",\"G3164\"]}', 'to fight against God');
INSERT INTO `lexicon_greek` (`id`, `strongs`, `word`, `data`, `usage`) VALUES
(2315, 2315, 'θεόπνευστος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"divinely breathed in\",\"long\":[\"inspired by God\",[\"the contents of the scriptures\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2316 and a presumed derivative of G4154\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈo.pnɛβ.stos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈow.pnef.stows\",\"sbl\":\"theopneustos\",\"dic\":\"theh-OH-pnev-stose\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-OH-pnayf-stose\"},\"see\":[\"G2316\",\"G4154\"]}', 'given by inspiration of God'),
(2316, 2316, 'θεός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a deity, especially (with G3588) the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; exceedingly (by Hebraism)\",\"long\":[\"a god or goddess, a general name of deities or divinities\",\"the Godhead, trinity\",[\"God the Father, the first person in the trinity\",\"Christ, the second person of the trinity\",\"Holy Spirit, the third person in the trinity\"],\"spoken of the only and true God\",[\"refers to the things of God\",\"his counsels, interests, things due to him\"],\"whatever can in any respect be likened unto God, or resemble him in any way\",[\"God\'s representative or viceregent\",[\"of magistrates and judges\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈows\",\"sbl\":\"theos\",\"dic\":\"theh-OSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-OSE\"},\"see\":[\"G3588\"]}', 'God, god(-ly, -ward), '),
(2317, 2317, 'θεοσέβεια', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"devoutness, i.e., piety\",\"long\":[\"reverence towards God\'s goodness\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2318\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.osˈɛ.βi.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.owsˈe̞.vi.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"theosebeia\",\"dic\":\"theh-ose-EH-vee-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ose-A-vee-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2318\"]}', 'godliness'),
(2318, 2318, 'θεοσεβής', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"reverent of God, i.e., pious\",\"long\":[\"worshipping God, pious\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2316 and G4576\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.os.ɛˈβes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.ows.e̞ˈve̞s\",\"sbl\":\"theosebēs\",\"dic\":\"theh-ose-eh-VASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ose-ay-VASE\"},\"see\":[\"G2316\",\"G4576\"]}', 'worshipper of God'),
(2319, 2319, 'θεοστυγής', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"hateful to God, i.e., impious\",\"long\":[\"hateful to God, exceptionally impious and wicked\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2316 and the base of G4767\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.os.tyˈɣes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.ows.tjuˈɣe̞s\",\"sbl\":\"theostygēs\",\"dic\":\"theh-ose-too-GASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ose-tyoo-GASE\"},\"see\":[\"G2316\",\"G4767\"]}', 'hater of God'),
(2320, 2320, 'θεότης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"divinity (abstractly)\",\"long\":[\"deity\",[\"the state of being God, Godhead\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2316\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈo.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"theotēs\",\"dic\":\"theh-OH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-OH-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2316\"]}', 'godhead'),
(2321, 2321, 'Θεόφιλος', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"friend of God\",\"short\":\"friend of God; Theophilus, a Christian\",\"long\":[\"the person to whom Luke addressed his Gospel and the book of Acts\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2316 and G5384\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈo.fi.los\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈow.fi.lows\",\"sbl\":\"theophilos\",\"dic\":\"theh-OH-fee-lose\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-OH-fee-lose\"},\"see\":[\"G2316\",\"G5384\"]}', 'Theophilus'),
(2322, 2322, 'θεραπεία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"attendance (specially, medical, i.e., cure); figuratively and collectively, domestics\",\"long\":[\"service rendered by one to another\",\"specifically medical service: curing, healing\",\"household service\",[\"body of attendants, servants, domestics\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2323\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.rɑˈpi.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.rɑˈpi.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"therapeia\",\"dic\":\"theh-ra-PEE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ra-PEE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2323\"]}', 'healing, household'),
(2323, 2323, 'θεραπεύω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to wait upon menially, i.e., (figuratively) to adore (God), or (specially) to relieve (of disease)\",\"long\":[\"to serve, do service\",\"to heal, cure, restore to health\"]},\"deriv\":\"from the same as G2324\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.rɑˈpɛβ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.rɑˈpev.ow\",\"sbl\":\"therapeuō\",\"dic\":\"theh-ra-PEV-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ra-PAVE-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2324\"]}', 'cure, heal, worship'),
(2324, 2324, 'θεράπων', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a menial attendant (as if cherishing)\",\"long\":[\"an attendant, servant: of God\",[\"spoken of Moses discharging the duties committed to him by God\"]]},\"deriv\":\"apparently a participle from an otherwise obsolete derivative of the base of G2330\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈrɑ.pon\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈrɑ.pown\",\"sbl\":\"therapōn\",\"dic\":\"theh-RA-pone\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-RA-pone\"},\"see\":[\"G2330\"]}', 'servant'),
(2325, 2325, 'θερίζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to harvest\",\"long\":[\"to reap, harvest\",\"proverbial expression for sowing and reaping\",\"cut off, destroy\",[\"as crops are cut down with a sickle\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2330 (in the sense of the crop)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛˈri.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈri.zow\",\"sbl\":\"therizō\",\"dic\":\"theh-REE-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-REE-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2330\"]}', 'reap'),
(2326, 2326, 'θερισμός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"reaping, i.e., the crop\",\"long\":[\"harvest, the act of reaping\",[\"figurative for the gathering of men into the kingdom of God\",\"referring to time of reaping, the final judgment, when the righteous are gathered into the kingdom of God and the wicked are cast into hell for ever\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2325\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.riˈsmos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.riˈsmows\",\"sbl\":\"therismos\",\"dic\":\"theh-ree-SMOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ree-SMOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2325\"]}', 'harvest'),
(2327, 2327, 'θεριστής', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a harvester\",\"long\":[\"a reaper\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2325\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.riˈstes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.riˈste̞s\",\"sbl\":\"theristēs\",\"dic\":\"theh-ree-STASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ree-STASE\"},\"see\":[\"G2325\"]}', 'reaper'),
(2328, 2328, 'θερμαίνω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to heat (oneself)\",\"long\":[\"to make warm, to heat\",\"to warm one\'s self\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2329\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛrˈmɛ.no\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞rˈme.now\",\"sbl\":\"thermainō\",\"dic\":\"ther-MEH-noh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thare-MAY-noh\"},\"see\":[\"G2329\"]}', '(be) warm(-ed) (self)'),
(2329, 2329, 'θέρμη', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"warmth\",\"long\":[\"heat\"]},\"deriv\":\"from the base of G2330\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɛr.me\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞r.me̞\",\"sbl\":\"thermē\",\"dic\":\"THER-may\",\"dic_mod\":\"THARE-may\"},\"see\":[\"G2330\"]}', 'heat'),
(2330, 2330, 'θέρος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"properly, heat, i.e., summer\",\"long\":[\"summer\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a primary θέρω (to heat)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθɛ.ros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞.rows\",\"sbl\":\"theros\",\"dic\":\"THEH-rose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAY-rose\"}}', 'summer'),
(2331, 2331, 'Θεσσαλονικεύς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a Thessalonican, i.e., inhabitant of Thessalonice\",\"long\":[\"a Thessalonians\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2332\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛs.sɑ.lo.niˈkɛβs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞s.sɑ.low.niˈcefs\",\"sbl\":\"thessalonikeus\",\"dic\":\"thes-sa-loh-nee-KEVS\",\"dic_mod\":\"thase-sa-loh-nee-KAYFS\"},\"see\":[\"G2332\"]}', 'Thessalonian'),
(2332, 2332, 'Θεσσαλονίκη', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"victory of falsity\",\"short\":\"Thessalonice, a place in Asia Minor\",\"long\":[\"a famous and populous city, situated on the Thermaic Gulf, the capital of the second division of Macedonia and the residence of a Roman governor and quaestor\"]},\"deriv\":\"from Θεσσαλός (a Thessalian) and G3529\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛs.sɑ.loˈni.ke\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞s.sɑ.lowˈni.ke̞\",\"sbl\":\"thessalonikē\",\"dic\":\"thes-sa-loh-NEE-kay\",\"dic_mod\":\"thase-sa-loh-NEE-kay\"},\"see\":[\"G3529\"]}', 'Thessalonica'),
(2333, 2333, 'Θευδᾶς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"God-given\",\"short\":\"Theudas, an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the name of an insurgent mentioned in Gamaliel\'s speech before the Jewish council at the time of the arraignment of the apostles\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛβˈðɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θevˈðɑs\",\"sbl\":\"theudas\",\"dic\":\"thev-THAHS\",\"dic_mod\":\"thave-THAHS\"},\"comment\":\"He appeared, according to Luke\'s account, at the head of about four hundred men. He was probably one of the insurrectionary chiefs or fanatics by whom the land was overrun in the last year of Herod\'s reign. Josephus speaks of a Theudas who played a similar part at the time of Claudius, about AD 44, but the Theudas mentioned by Luke must be a different person from the one spoken of by Josephus.\"}', 'Theudas'),
(2334, 2334, 'θεωρέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to be a spectator of, i.e., discern, (literally, figuratively (experience) or intensively (acknowledge))\",\"long\":[\"to be a spectator, look at, behold\",[\"to view attentively, take a view of, survey\",[\"to view mentally, consider\"]],\"to see\",[\"to perceive with the eyes, to enjoy the presence of one\",\"to discern, descry\",\"to ascertain, find out by seeing\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of G2300 (perhaps by addition of G3708)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.oˈrɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.owˈre̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"theōreō\",\"dic\":\"theh-oh-REH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-oh-RAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2300\",\"G3700\",\"G3708\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G3700.\"}', 'behold, consider, look on, perceive, see'),
(2335, 2335, 'θεωρία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"spectatorship, i.e., (concretely) a spectacle\",\"long\":[\"a viewing, beholding\",\"that which is viewed, a spectacle, sight\"]},\"deriv\":\"from the same as G2334\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θɛ.oˈri.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.owˈri.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"theōria\",\"dic\":\"theh-oh-REE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-oh-REE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2334\"]}', 'sight'),
(2336, 2336, 'θήκη', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a receptacle, i.e., scabbard\",\"long\":[\"that which a thing is put or laid away, a receptacle, repository, chest, box\",[\"used of the sheath of a sword\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G5087\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθe.ke\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞.ke̞\",\"sbl\":\"thēkē\",\"dic\":\"THAY-kay\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAY-kay\"},\"see\":[\"G5087\"]}', 'sheath'),
(2337, 2337, 'θηλάζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to suckle, (by implication) to suck\",\"long\":[\"to give the breast, give suck, to suckle\",\"to suck\"]},\"deriv\":\"from θηλή (the nipple)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θeˈlɑ.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈlɑ.zow\",\"sbl\":\"thēlazō\",\"dic\":\"thay-LA-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-LA-zoh\"}}', '(give) suck(-ling)'),
(2338, 2338, 'θῆλυς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"female\",\"long\":[\"of the female sex\",\"a woman, a female\"]},\"deriv\":\"from the same as G2337\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθe.lys\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞.ljus\",\"sbl\":\"thēlys\",\"dic\":\"THAY-loos\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAY-lyoos\"},\"see\":[\"G2337\"]}', 'female, woman'),
(2339, 2339, 'θήρα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"hunting, i.e., (figuratively) destruction\",\"long\":[\"a hunting of wild beasts to destroy them\",\"metaphorically of preparing destruction for men\"]},\"deriv\":\"from θήρ (a wild animal, as game)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθe.rɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθe̞.rɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thēra\",\"dic\":\"THAY-ra\",\"dic_mod\":\"THAY-ra\"}}', 'trap'),
(2340, 2340, 'θηρεύω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to hunt (an animal), i.e., (figuratively) to carp at\",\"long\":[\"to go a hunting, to hunt, to catch in hunting\",\"metaphorically to lay wait for, strive to ensnare, catch artfully\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2339\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θeˈrɛβ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈrev.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thēreuō\",\"dic\":\"thay-REV-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-RAVE-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2339\"]}', 'catch'),
(2341, 2341, 'θηριομαχέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to be a beast-fighter (in the gladiatorial show), i.e., (figuratively) to encounter (furious men)\",\"long\":[\"to fight with wild beasts\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a compound of G2342 and G3164\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θe.ri.o.mɑˈxɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.ri.ow.mɑˈxe̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thēriomacheō\",\"dic\":\"thay-ree-oh-ma-HEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-ree-oh-ma-HAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2342\",\"G3164\"]}', 'fight with wild beasts'),
(2342, 2342, 'θηρίον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a dangerous animal\",\"long\":[\"an animal\",\"a wild animal, wild beast, beast\",\"metaphorically a brutal, bestial man, savage, ferocious\"]},\"deriv\":\"diminutive from the same as G2339\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θeˈri.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞ˈri.own\",\"sbl\":\"thērion\",\"dic\":\"thay-REE-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-REE-one\"},\"see\":[\"G2339\"]}', '(venomous, wild) beast'),
(2343, 2343, 'θησαυρίζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to amass or reserve (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to gather and lay up, to heap up, store up\",[\"to accumulate riches\",\"to keep in store, store up, reserve\"],\"metaphorically so to live from day to day as to increase either the bitterness or the happiness of one\'s consequent lot\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2344\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θe.sɛβˈri.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.saˈri.zow\",\"sbl\":\"thēsaurizō\",\"dic\":\"thay-sev-REE-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-sa-REE-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2344\"]}', 'lay up (treasure), (keep) in store, (heap) treasure (together, up)'),
(2344, 2344, 'θησαυρός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a deposit, i.e., wealth (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"the place in which good and precious things are collected and laid up\",[\"a casket, coffer, or other receptacle, in which valuables are kept\",\"a treasury\",\"storehouse, repository, magazine\"],\"the things laid up in a treasury, collected treasures\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G5087\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θe.sɛβˈros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θe̞.saˈrows\",\"sbl\":\"thēsauros\",\"dic\":\"thay-sev-ROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thay-sa-ROSE\"},\"see\":[\"G5087\"]}', 'treasure'),
(2345, 2345, 'θιγγάνω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to manipulate, i.e., have to do with; by implication, to injure\",\"long\":[\"to touch, handle\",[\"to do violence to, injury\"]]},\"deriv\":\"a prolonged form of an obsolete primary θίγω (to finger)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θiŋˈɣɑ.no\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θiŋˈɣɑ.now\",\"sbl\":\"thinganō\",\"dic\":\"theeng-GA-noh\",\"dic_mod\":\"theeng-GA-noh\"}}', 'handle, touch'),
(2346, 2346, 'θλίβω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to crowd (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to press (as grapes), press hard upon\",\"a compressed way\",[\"narrow straitened, contracted\"],\"metaphorically to trouble, afflict, distress\"]},\"deriv\":\"akin to the base of G5147\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθli.βo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθli.vow\",\"sbl\":\"thlibō\",\"dic\":\"THLEE-voh\",\"dic_mod\":\"THLEE-voh\"},\"see\":[\"G5147\"]}', 'afflict, narrow, throng, suffer tribulation, trouble'),
(2347, 2347, 'θλῖψις', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"pressure (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"a pressing, pressing together, pressure\",\"metaphorically oppression, affliction, tribulation, distress, straits\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2346\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθli.p͡sis\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθli.p͡sis\",\"sbl\":\"thlipsis\",\"dic\":\"THLEE-psees\",\"dic_mod\":\"THLEE-psees\"},\"see\":[\"G2346\"]}', 'afflicted(-tion), anguish, burdened, persecution, tribulation, trouble'),
(2348, 2348, 'θνήσκω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to die (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to die, to be dead\",\"metaphorically to be spiritually dead\"]},\"deriv\":\"a strengthened form of a simpler primary θάνω <pronunciation strongs=\\\"than\'-o\\\"/> (which is used for it only in certain tenses)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθne.sko\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθne̞.skow\",\"sbl\":\"thnēskō\",\"dic\":\"THNAY-skoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"THNAY-skoh\"}}', 'be dead, die'),
(2349, 2349, 'θνητός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"liable to die\",\"long\":[\"liable to death, mortal\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2348\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θneˈtos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θne̞ˈtows\",\"sbl\":\"thnētos\",\"dic\":\"thnay-TOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thnay-TOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2348\"]}', 'mortal(-ity)'),
(2350, 2350, 'θορυβέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to be in tumult, i.e., disturb, clamor\",\"long\":[\"to make a noise or uproar, be turbulent\",\"to disturb, throw into confusion\",[\"to be troubled in mind\",\"to wail tumultuously\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2351\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θo.ryˈβɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θow.rjuˈve̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thorybeō\",\"dic\":\"thoh-roo-VEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thoh-ryoo-VAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2351\"]}', 'make ado (a noise), trouble self, set on an uproar'),
(2351, 2351, 'θόρυβος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a disturbance\",\"long\":[\"a noise, tumult, uproar\",[\"of persons wailing\",\"of a clamorous and excited multitude\",\"of riotous persons\"],\"a tumult, as a breach of public order\"]},\"deriv\":\"from the base of G2360\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθo.ry.βos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθow.rju.vows\",\"sbl\":\"thorybos\",\"dic\":\"THOH-roo-vose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THOH-ryoo-vose\"},\"see\":[\"G2360\"]}', 'tumult, uproar'),
(2352, 2352, 'θραύω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to crush\",\"long\":[\"to break, break in pieces, shatter, smite through\"]},\"deriv\":\"a primary verb\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθrɛβ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθra.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thrauō\",\"dic\":\"THREV-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"THRA-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G4486\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G4486.\"}', 'bruise'),
(2353, 2353, 'θρέμμα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"stock (as raised on a farm)\",\"long\":[\"whatever is fed or nursed\",[\"a ward, nursling, child\"],\"a flock, cattle, especially sheep and goats\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G5142\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθrɛm.mɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθre̞m.mɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thremma\",\"dic\":\"THREM-ma\",\"dic_mod\":\"THRAME-ma\"},\"see\":[\"G5142\"]}', 'cattle'),
(2354, 2354, 'θρηνέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to bewail\",\"long\":[\"to mourn, to lament\",[\"of singers of dirges, [to wail]\"],\"to bewail, deplore\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2355\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θreˈnɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θre̞ˈne̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thrēneō\",\"dic\":\"thray-NEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thray-NAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2355\"]}', 'lament, mourn'),
(2355, 2355, 'θρῆνος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"wailing\",\"long\":[\"a lamentation\"]},\"deriv\":\"from the base of G2360\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθre.nos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθre̞.nows\",\"sbl\":\"thrēnos\",\"dic\":\"THRAY-nose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THRAY-nose\"},\"see\":[\"G2360\"]}', 'lamentation'),
(2356, 2356, 'θρησκεία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"ceremonial observance\",\"long\":[\"religious worship\",[\"especially external, that which consists of ceremonies\",[\"religious discipline, religion\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of G2357\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θreˈski.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θre̞ˈsci.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thrēskeia\",\"dic\":\"thray-SKEE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"thray-SKEE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2357\"]}', 'religion, worshipping'),
(2357, 2357, 'θρησκός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"ceremonious in worship (as demonstrative), i.e., pious\",\"long\":[\"fearing or worshipping God\",\"to tremble\",[\"trembling, fearful\"]]},\"deriv\":\"probably from the base of G2360\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θreˈskos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θre̞ˈskows\",\"sbl\":\"thrēskos\",\"dic\":\"thray-SKOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thray-SKOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2360\"]}', 'religious'),
(2358, 2358, 'θριαμβεύω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and a derivative of G0680 (meaning a noisy iambus, a hymn sung in festal processions in honor of the god Bacchus); to make an acclamatory procession, i.e., (figuratively) to conquer or (by Hebraism) to give victory\",\"long\":[\"to triumph, to celebrate a triumph\",\"cause one to triumph\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a prolonged compound of the base of G2360\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θri.ɑmˈβɛβ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θri.ɑɱˈvev.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thriambeuō\",\"dic\":\"three-am-VEV-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"three-am-VAVE-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G0680\",\"G2360\"]}', '(cause) to triumph (over)'),
(2359, 2359, 'θρίξ', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"of uncertain derivation; hair\",\"long\":[\"the hair of the head\",\"the hair of animals\"]},\"deriv\":\"genitive case τριχός, etc\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θrik͡s\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θrik͡s\",\"sbl\":\"thrix\",\"dic\":\"threeks\",\"dic_mod\":\"threeks\"},\"see\":[\"G2864\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G2864.\"}', 'hair'),
(2360, 2360, 'θροέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to clamor, i.e., (by implication) to frighten\",\"long\":[\"to cry aloud, make a noise by outcry\",[\"in the New Testament, to trouble, frighten\",\"to be troubled in mind, to be frightened, alarmed\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from θρέομαι to wail\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θroˈɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θrowˈe̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"throeō\",\"dic\":\"throh-EH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"throh-A-oh\"}}', 'trouble'),
(2361, 2361, 'θρόμβος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a clot\",\"long\":[\"a large thick drop, especially of clotted blood\"]},\"deriv\":\"perhaps from G5142 (in the sense of thickening)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθrom.βos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθrowɱ.vows\",\"sbl\":\"thrombos\",\"dic\":\"THROME-vose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THROME-vose\"},\"see\":[\"G5142\"]}', 'great drop'),
(2362, 2362, 'θρόνος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a stately seat (\\\"throne\\\"); by implication, power or (concretely) a potentate\",\"long\":[\"a throne seat\",[\"a chair of state having a footstool\",\"assigned in the New Testament to kings, hence, kingly power or royalty\",[\"metaphorically to God, the governor of the world\",\"to the Messiah, Christ, the partner and assistant in the divine administration\",[\"hence divine power belonging to Christ\"],\"to judges i.e., tribunal or bench\",\"to elders\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"from θράω (to sit)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθro.nos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθrow.nows\",\"sbl\":\"thronos\",\"dic\":\"THROH-nose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THROH-nose\"}}', 'seat, throne'),
(2363, 2363, 'Θυάτειρα', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"odor of affliction\",\"short\":\"Thyatira, a place in Asia Minor\",\"long\":[\"a colony of Macedonia Greeks, situated between Sardis and Pergamos on the river Lycus; its inhabitants gained their living by traffic and the art of dyeing in purple\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain derivation\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θyˈɑ.ti.rɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θjuˈɑ.ti.rɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thyateira\",\"dic\":\"thoo-AH-tee-ra\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-AH-tee-ra\"}}', 'Thyatira'),
(2364, 2364, 'θυγάτηρ', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a female child, or (by Hebraism) descendant (or inhabitant)\",\"long\":[\"a daughter\",[\"a daughter of God\",[\"acceptable to God, rejoicing in God\'s peculiar care and protection\"],\"with the name of a place, city, or region\",[\"denotes collectively all its inhabitants and citizens\"],\"a female descendant\"]]},\"deriv\":\"apparently a primary word (compare \\\"daughter\\\")\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θyˈɣɑ.ter\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θjuˈɣɑ.te̞r\",\"sbl\":\"thygatēr\",\"dic\":\"thoo-GA-tare\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-GA-tare\"}}', 'daughter'),
(2365, 2365, 'θυγάτριον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a daughterling\",\"long\":[\"a little daughter\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2364\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θyˈɣɑ.tri.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θjuˈɣɑ.tri.own\",\"sbl\":\"thygatrion\",\"dic\":\"thoo-GA-tree-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-GA-tree-one\"},\"see\":[\"G2364\"]}', 'little (young) daughter'),
(2366, 2366, 'θύελλα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a storm\",\"long\":[\"a sudden storm, tempest, whirlwind\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2380 (in the sense of blowing) a storm\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθy.ɛl.lɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθju.e̞l.lɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thyella\",\"dic\":\"THOO-el-la\",\"dic_mod\":\"THYOO-ale-la\"},\"see\":[\"G2380\"]}', 'tempest'),
(2367, 2367, 'θύϊνος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"made of citron-wood\",\"long\":[\"the citrus, an odoriferous North African tree used as incense, prized by the ancient Greeks and Romans on account of the beauty of its wood for various ornamental purposes\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of G2380 (in the sense of blowing; denoting a certain fragrant tree)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθy.i.nos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθju.i.nows\",\"sbl\":\"thyinos\",\"dic\":\"THOO-ee-nose\",\"dic_mod\":\"THYOO-ee-nose\"},\"see\":[\"G2380\"]}', 'thyine'),
(2368, 2368, 'θυμίαμα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"an aroma, i.e., fragrant powder burnt in religious service; by implication, the burning itself\",\"long\":[\"an aromatic substance burnt, incense\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2370\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θyˈmi.ɑ.mɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θjuˈmi.ɑ.mɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thymiama\",\"dic\":\"thoo-MEE-ah-ma\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-MEE-ah-ma\"},\"see\":[\"G2370\"]}', 'incense, odour'),
(2369, 2369, 'θυμιαστήριον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a place of fumigation, i.e., the alter of incense (in the Temple)\",\"long\":[\"a utensil for fumigating or burning incense\",\"an altar of incense\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of G2370\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θy.mi.ɑˈste.ri.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θju.mi.ɑˈste̞.ri.own\",\"sbl\":\"thymiastērion\",\"dic\":\"thoo-mee-ah-STAY-ree-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-mee-ah-STAY-ree-one\"},\"see\":[\"G2370\"]}', 'censer'),
(2370, 2370, 'θυμιάω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to fumigate, i.e., offer aromatic fumes\",\"long\":[\"to burn incense\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of G2380 (in the sense of smoking)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θy.miˈɑ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θju.miˈɑ.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thymiaō\",\"dic\":\"thoo-mee-AH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-mee-AH-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2380\"]}', 'burn incense'),
(2371, 2371, 'θυμομαχέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to be in a furious fight, i.e., (figuratively) to be exasperated\",\"long\":[\"to carry on war with great animosity\",\"to be very angry, be exasperated\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a presumed compound of G2372 and G3164\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θy.mo.mɑˈxɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θju.mow.mɑˈxe̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thymomacheō\",\"dic\":\"thoo-moh-ma-HEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-moh-ma-HAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2372\",\"G3164\"]}', 'be highly displeased'),
(2372, 2372, 'θυμός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"passion (as if breathing hard)\",\"long\":[\"passion, angry, heat, anger forthwith boiling up and soon subsiding again\",\"glow, ardour, the wine of passion, inflaming wine (which either drives the drinker mad or kills him with its strength)\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2380\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θyˈmos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θjuˈmows\",\"sbl\":\"thymos\",\"dic\":\"thoo-MOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-MOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2380\",\"G5590\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G5590.\"}', 'fierceness, indignation, wrath'),
(2373, 2373, 'θυμόω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to put in a passion, i.e., enrage\",\"long\":[\"to cause one to become incensed, to provoke to anger\",\"to be wroth\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2372\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θyˈmo.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θjuˈmow.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thymoō\",\"dic\":\"thoo-MOH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-MOH-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2372\"]}', 'be wroth'),
(2374, 2374, 'θύρα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a portal or entrance (the opening or the closure, literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"a door\",[\"the vestibule\",\"used of any opening like a door, an entrance, way or passage into\",\"in a parable or metaphor\",[\"the door through which sheep go in and out, the name of him who brings salvation to those who follow his guidance\",\"\\\"an open door\\\" is used of the opportunity of doing something\",\"the door of the kingdom of heaven (likened to a palace) denotes the conditions which must be complied with in order to be received into the kingdom of God\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"apparently a primary word (compare \\\"door\\\")\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθy.rɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθju.rɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thyra\",\"dic\":\"THOO-ra\",\"dic_mod\":\"THYOO-ra\"}}', 'door, gate'),
(2375, 2375, 'θυρεός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a large shield (as door-shaped)\",\"long\":[\"a shield, a large oblong, four cornered shield\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2374\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θy.rɛˈos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θju.re̞ˈows\",\"sbl\":\"thyreos\",\"dic\":\"thoo-reh-OSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-ray-OSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2374\"]}', 'shield'),
(2376, 2376, 'θυρίς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"an aperture, i.e., window\",\"long\":[\"a window\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2374\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θyˈris\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θjuˈris\",\"sbl\":\"thyris\",\"dic\":\"thoo-REES\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-REES\"},\"see\":[\"G2374\"]}', 'window'),
(2377, 2377, 'θυρωρός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a gate- warden\",\"long\":[\"a doorkeeper, porter\",[\"a male or female janitor\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2374 and οὖρος (a watcher)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θy.roˈros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θju.rowˈrows\",\"sbl\":\"thyrōros\",\"dic\":\"thoo-roh-ROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-roh-ROSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2374\"]}', 'that kept the door, porter'),
(2378, 2378, 'θυσία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"sacrifice (the act or the victim, literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"a sacrifice, victim\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2380\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θyˈsi.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θjuˈsi.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"thysia\",\"dic\":\"thoo-SEE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-SEE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2380\"]}', 'sacrifice'),
(2379, 2379, 'θυσιαστήριον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a place of sacrifice, i.e., an altar (special or genitive case, literal or figurative)\",\"long\":[\"the altar for slaying and burning of victims used of\",[\"the altar of whole burnt offerings which stood in the court of the priests in the temple at Jerusalem\",\"the altar of incense which stood in the sanctuary or the Holy Place\",\"any other altar\",[\"metaphorically, the cross on which Christ suffered an expiatory death: to eat of this altar i.e., to appropriate to one\'s self the fruits of Christ\'s expiatory death\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of G2378\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θy.si.ɑˈste.ri.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θju.si.ɑˈste̞.ri.own\",\"sbl\":\"thysiastērion\",\"dic\":\"thoo-see-ah-STAY-ree-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"thyoo-see-ah-STAY-ree-one\"},\"see\":[\"G2378\"]}', 'altar'),
(2380, 2380, 'θύω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"properly, to rush (breathe hard, blow, smoke), i.e., (by implication) to sacrifice (properly, by fire, but genitive case); by extension to immolate (slaughter for any purpose)\",\"long\":[\"to sacrifice, immolate\",\"to slay, kill\",[\"of the paschal lamb\"],\"slaughter\"]},\"deriv\":\"a primary verb\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθy.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθju.ow\",\"sbl\":\"thyō\",\"dic\":\"THOO-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"THYOO-oh\"}}', 'kill, (do) sacrifice, slay'),
(2381, 2381, 'Θωμᾶς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"a twin\",\"short\":\"the twin; Thomas, a Christian\",\"long\":[\"one of the apostles\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Chaldee origin (compare H8380)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"θoˈmɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"θowˈmɑs\",\"sbl\":\"thōmas\",\"dic\":\"thoh-MAHS\",\"dic_mod\":\"thoh-MAHS\"},\"see\":[\"H8380\"]}', 'Thomas'),
(2382, 2382, 'θώραξ', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"the chest (\\\"thorax\\\"), i.e., (by implication) a corslet\",\"long\":[\"the breast, the part of the body from the neck to the navel, where the ribs end\",\"a breastplate or corset consisting of two parts and protecting the body on both sides from the neck to the middle\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈθo.rɑk͡s\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈθow.rɑk͡s\",\"sbl\":\"thōrax\",\"dic\":\"THOH-rahks\",\"dic_mod\":\"THOH-rahks\"}}', 'breast-plate'),
(2383, 2383, 'Ἰάειρος', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"whom God enlightens\",\"short\":\"Jairus (i.e., Jair), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"a ruler of a synagogue, probably near the western shore of the Sea of Galilee\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H2971)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈɑ.i.ros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈɑ.i.rows\",\"sbl\":\"iaeiros\",\"dic\":\"ee-AH-ee-rose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-AH-ee-rose\"},\"see\":[\"H2971\"]}', 'Jairus'),
(2384, 2384, 'Ἰακώβ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"heel-catcher, supplanter\",\"short\":\"Jacob (i.e., Ja`akob), the progenitor of the Israelites\",\"long\":[\"was the second son of Isaac\",\"the father of Joseph, the husband of Mary\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3290)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɑˈkoβ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ɑˈkowv\",\"sbl\":\"iakōb\",\"dic\":\"ee-ah-KOVE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ah-KOVE\"},\"see\":[\"H3290\"]}', 'also an Israelite:--Jacob'),
(2385, 2385, 'Ἰάκωβος', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"supplanter\",\"short\":\"Jacobus, the name of three Israelites\",\"long\":[\"son of Zebedee, an apostle and brother of the apostle John, commonly called James the greater or elder, slain by Herod, Acts 12\",\"an apostle, son of Alphaeus, called the less\",\"James the half-brother of Christ\",\"an unknown James, father of the apostle Judas(?)\"]},\"deriv\":\"the same as G2384 Graecized\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈɑ.ko.βos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈɑ.kow.vows\",\"sbl\":\"iakōbos\",\"dic\":\"ee-AH-koh-vose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-AH-koh-vose\"},\"see\":[\"G2384\"]}', 'James'),
(2386, 2386, 'ἴαμα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a cure (the effect)\",\"long\":[\"a means of healing, remedy, medicine\",\"a healing\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2390\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.ɑ.mɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.ɑ.mɑ\",\"sbl\":\"iama\",\"dic\":\"EE-ah-ma\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-ah-ma\"},\"see\":[\"G2390\"]}', 'healing'),
(2387, 2387, 'Ἰαμβρῆς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"foamy healer\",\"short\":\"Jambres, an Egyptian\",\"long\":[\"Jambres, one of Pharaoh\'s magicians who attempted to replicate Moses\' miracles in the Old Testament\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Egyptian origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɑmˈβres\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ɑɱˈvre̞s\",\"sbl\":\"iambrēs\",\"dic\":\"ee-am-VRASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-am-VRASE\"},\"comment\":\"He and Jannes, were two Egyptian magicians who in the presence of Pharaoh imitated the miracles of Aaron in order to destroy his influence with the king. Paul derived their names from the tradition of the Talmudists and the Rabbins.\"}', 'Jambres'),
(2388, 2388, 'Ἰαννά', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"flourishing\",\"short\":\"Janna, an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"son of Joseph and the father of Melchi, in the genealogy of Christ\"]},\"deriv\":\"probably of Hebrew origin (compare H3238)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɑnˈnɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ɑnˈnɑ\",\"sbl\":\"ianna\",\"dic\":\"ee-an-NA\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-an-NA\"},\"see\":[\"H3238\"]}', 'Janna'),
(2389, 2389, 'Ἰαννῆς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"he vexed\",\"short\":\"Jannes, an Egyptian\",\"long\":[\"Jannes, one of Pharaoh\'s magicians who attempted to replicate Moses\' miracles in the Old Testament\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Egyptian origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɑnˈnes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ɑnˈne̞s\",\"sbl\":\"iannēs\",\"dic\":\"ee-an-NASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-an-NASE\"},\"comment\":\"He and Jambres, were two Egyptian magicians who in the presence of Pharaoh imitated the miracles of Aaron in order to destroy his influence with the king. Paul derived their names from the tradition of the Talmudists and the Rabbins\"}', 'Jannes'),
(2390, 2390, 'ἰάομαι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to cure (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to cure, heal\",\"to make whole\",[\"to free from errors and sins, to bring about (one\'s) salvation\"]]},\"deriv\":\"middle voice of apparently a primary verb\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈɑ.o.mɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈɑ.ow.me\",\"sbl\":\"iaomai\",\"dic\":\"ee-AH-oh-meh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-AH-oh-may\"}}', 'heal, make whole'),
(2391, 2391, 'Ἰάρεδ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"descent\",\"short\":\"Jared (i.e., Jered), an antediluvian\",\"long\":[\"one of the antediluvian patriarchs, the father of Enoch\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3382)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈɑ.rɛð\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈɑ.re̞ð\",\"sbl\":\"iared\",\"dic\":\"ee-AH-reth\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-AH-rayth\"},\"see\":[\"H3382\"]}', 'Jared'),
(2392, 2392, 'ἴασις', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"curing (the act)\",\"long\":[\"a healing, cure\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2390\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.ɑ.sis\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.ɑ.sis\",\"sbl\":\"iasis\",\"dic\":\"EE-ah-sees\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-ah-sees\"},\"see\":[\"G2390\"]}', 'cure, heal(-ing)'),
(2393, 2393, 'ἴασπις', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"\\\"jasper\\\", a gem\",\"long\":[\"jasper, a precious stone of various colors (for some are purple, others blue, others green, and others the color of brass)\"]},\"deriv\":\"probably of foreign origin (see H3471)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.ɑ.spis\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.ɑ.spis\",\"sbl\":\"iaspis\",\"dic\":\"EE-ah-spees\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-ah-spees\"},\"see\":[\"H3471\"]}', 'jasper'),
(2394, 2394, 'Ἰάσων', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"one who will heal\",\"short\":\"about to cure; Jason, a Christian\",\"long\":[\"a Thessalonians who entertained Paul and Silas, and maybe a cousin of Paul (Romans 16:21)\"]},\"deriv\":\"future active participle masculine of G2390\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈɑ.son\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈɑ.sown\",\"sbl\":\"iasōn\",\"dic\":\"ee-AH-sone\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-AH-sone\"},\"see\":[\"G2390\"]}', 'Jason'),
(2395, 2395, 'ἰατρός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a physician\",\"long\":[\"a physician\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2390\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɑˈtros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ɑˈtrows\",\"sbl\":\"iatros\",\"dic\":\"ee-ah-TROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ah-TROSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2390\"]}', 'physician'),
(2396, 2396, 'ἴδε', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"used as an interjection to denote surprise; lo!\",\"long\":[\"behold, see\"]},\"deriv\":\"second person singular imperative active of G1492\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.ðɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.ðe̞\",\"sbl\":\"ide\",\"dic\":\"EE-theh\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-thay\"},\"see\":[\"G1492\"]}', 'behold, lo, see'),
(2397, 2397, 'ἰδέα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a sight (comparative figuratively \\\"idea\\\"), i.e., aspect\",\"long\":[\"form, external appearance\",\"aspect, look\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G1492\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈðɛ.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈðe̞.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"idea\",\"dic\":\"ee-THEH-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-THAY-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G1492\"]}', 'countenance'),
(2398, 2398, 'ἴδιος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"pertaining to self, i.e., one\'s own; by implication, private or separate\",\"long\":[\"pertaining to one\'s self, one\'s own, belonging to one\'s self\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.ði.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.ði.ows\",\"sbl\":\"idios\",\"dic\":\"EE-thee-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-thee-ose\"}}', 'X his acquaintance, when they were alone, apart, aside, due, his (own, proper, several), home, (her, our, thine, your) own (business), private(-ly), proper, severally, their (own)'),
(2399, 2399, 'ἰδιώτης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a private person, i.e., (by implication) an ignoramus (compare \\\"idiot\\\")\",\"long\":[\"a private person as opposed to a magistrate, ruler, king\",\"a common soldier, as opposed to a military officer\",\"a writer of prose as opposed to a poet\",\"in the New Testament, an unlearned, illiterate, man as opposed to the learned and educated: one who is unskilled in any art\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2398\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ðiˈo.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ðiˈow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"idiōtēs\",\"dic\":\"ee-thee-OH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-thee-OH-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2398\"]}', 'ignorant, rude, unlearned'),
(2400, 2400, 'ἰδού', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"used as imperative lo!\",\"long\":[\"behold, see, lo\"]},\"deriv\":\"second person singular imperative middle voice of G1492\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈðu\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈðu\",\"sbl\":\"idou\",\"dic\":\"ee-THOO\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-THOO\"},\"see\":[\"G1492\"]}', 'behold, lo, see'),
(2401, 2401, 'Ἰδουμαία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"Idumaea (i.e., Edom), a region East (and South) of Palestine\",\"long\":[\"Idumaea, the name of a region between southern Palestine and the Arabian Petraea inhabited by Edom or Esau and his posterity\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H0123)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ðuˈmɛ.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ðuˈme.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"idoumaia\",\"dic\":\"ee-thoo-MEH-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-thoo-MAY-ah\"},\"see\":[\"H0123\"]}', 'Idumaea'),
(2402, 2402, 'ἱδρώς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"perspiration\",\"long\":[\"sweat\"]},\"deriv\":\"a strengthened form of a primary idos (sweat)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hiˈðros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈðrows\",\"sbl\":\"hidrōs\",\"dic\":\"hee-THROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-THROSE\"}}', 'sweat'),
(2403, 2403, 'Ἰεζαβήλ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"chaste\",\"short\":\"Jezabel (i.e., Jezebel), a Tyrian woman (used as a synonym of a termagant or false teacher)\",\"long\":[\"wife of Ahab, an impious and cruel queen who protected idolatry and persecuted the prophets\",\"the symbolic name of a woman who pretended to be a prophetess, and who, addicted to antinomianism, claimed Christian liberty of eating things sacrificed to idols\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H0348)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɛ.zɑˈβel\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.zɑˈve̞l\",\"sbl\":\"iezabēl\",\"dic\":\"ee-eh-za-VALE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-za-VALE\"},\"see\":[\"H0348\"]}', 'Jezabel'),
(2404, 2404, 'Ἱεράπολις', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"holy city\",\"short\":\"holy city; Hierapolis, a place in Asia Minor\",\"long\":[\"a city of Phrygia, situated above the junction of the rivers Lycus and Maeander, near Colosse and Laodicea\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2413 and G4172\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛˈrɑ.po.lis\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞ˈrɑ.pow.lis\",\"sbl\":\"hierapolis\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-RA-poh-lees\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-RA-poh-lees\"},\"see\":[\"G2413\",\"G4172\"]}', 'Hierapolis'),
(2405, 2405, 'ἱερατεία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"priestliness, i.e., the sacerdotal function\",\"long\":[\"the priesthood, the office of a priest\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2407\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.rɑˈti.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.rɑˈti.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"hierateia\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-ra-TEE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-ra-TEE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2407\"]}', 'office of the priesthood, priest\'s office'),
(2406, 2406, 'ἱεράτευμα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"the priestly fraternity, i.e., sacerdotal order (figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"the office of a priest\",\"the order or body of priests\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2407\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛˈrɑ.tɛβ.mɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞ˈrɑ.tev.mɑ\",\"sbl\":\"hierateuma\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-RA-tev-ma\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-RA-tave-ma\"},\"see\":[\"G2407\"]}', 'priesthood'),
(2407, 2407, 'ἱερατεύω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to be a priest, i.e., perform his functions\",\"long\":[\"to be a priest, discharge the office of a priest, to be busied in sacred duties\"]},\"deriv\":\"prolongation from G2409\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.rɑˈtɛβ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.rɑˈtev.ow\",\"sbl\":\"hierateuō\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-ra-TEV-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-ra-TAVE-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2409\"]}', 'execute the priest\'s office'),
(2408, 2408, 'Ἱερεμίας', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"whom Jehovah has appointed\",\"short\":\"Hieremias (i.e., Jermijah), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the Old Testament prophet Jeremiah\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3414)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.rɛˈmi.ɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.re̞ˈmi.ɑs\",\"sbl\":\"hieremias\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-reh-MEE-as\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-ray-MEE-as\"},\"see\":[\"H3414\"],\"comment\":\"Jeremiah was the son of Hilkiah of the priests that were in Anathoth. He was called very young (in 626 BC) to the prophetic office, and prophesied for 42 years. He probably died in Egypt.\"}', 'Jeremiah'),
(2409, 2409, 'ἱερεύς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a priest (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"a priest, one who offers sacrifices and in general in busied with sacred rites\",[\"referring to priests of Gentiles or the Jews,\"],\"metaphorically of Christians, because, purified by the blood of Christ and brought into close intercourse with God, they devote their life to him alone and to Christ\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2413\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛˈrɛβs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞ˈrefs\",\"sbl\":\"hiereus\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-REVS\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-RAYFS\"},\"see\":[\"G2413\"]}', '(high) priest'),
(2410, 2410, 'Ἱεριχώ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"place of fragrance\",\"short\":\"Jericho, a place in Palestine\",\"long\":[\"Jericho, a noted city\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3405)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.riˈxo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.riˈxow\",\"sbl\":\"hierichō\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-ree-HOH\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-ree-HOH\"},\"see\":[\"H3405\"],\"comment\":\"Jericho was abounding in balsam, honey, cyprus, myrobalanus, roses and other fragrant products. It was near the north shore of the Dead Sea in the tribe of Benjamin, between Jerusalem and the Jordan River.\"}', 'Jericho'),
(2411, 2411, 'ἱερόν', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a sacred place, i.e., the entire precincts (whereas G3485 denotes the central sanctuary itself) of the Temple (at Jerusalem or elsewhere)\",\"long\":[\"a sacred place, temple\",[\"used of the temple of Artemis at Ephesus\",\"used of the temple at Jerusalem\"]]},\"deriv\":\"neuter of G2413\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛˈron\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞ˈrown\",\"sbl\":\"hieron\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-RONE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-RONE\"},\"see\":[\"G2413\",\"G3485\"],\"comment\":\"The temple of Jerusalem consisted of the whole of the sacred enclosure, embracing the entire aggregate of buildings, balconies, porticos, courts (that is that of the men of Israel, that of the women, and that of the priests), belonging to the temple; the latter designates the sacred edifice properly so called, consisting of two parts, the \\\"sanctuary\\\" or \\\"Holy Place\\\" (which no one except the priests was allowed to enter), and the \\\"Holy of Holies\\\" or \\\"the most holy place\\\" (which was entered only on the great day of atonement by the high priest alone). Also there were the courts where Jesus or the apostles taught or encountered adversaries; also the courts of the temple out of which Jesus drove the buyers and sellers and the money changers, court of the women.\"}', 'temple'),
(2412, 2412, 'ἱεροπρεπής', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"reverent\",\"long\":[\"befitting men, places, actions or sacred things to God\",\"reverent\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2413 and the same as G4241\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.ro.prɛˈpes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.row.pre̞ˈpe̞s\",\"sbl\":\"hieroprepēs\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-roh-preh-PASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-roh-pray-PASE\"},\"see\":[\"G2413\",\"G4241\"]}', 'as becometh holiness'),
(2413, 2413, 'ἱερός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"sacred\",\"long\":[\"sacred, consecrated to the deity, pertaining to God\",[\"sacred Scriptures, because inspired by God, treating of divine things and therefore to be devoutly revered\"]]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛˈros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞ˈrows\",\"sbl\":\"hieros\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-ROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-ROSE\"}}', 'holy'),
(2414, 2414, 'Ἱεροσόλυμα', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"set ye double peace\",\"short\":\"Hierosolyma (i.e., Jerushalaim), the capitol of Palestine\",\"long\":[\"denotes either the city itself or the inhabitants\",\"\\\"the Jerusalem that now is\\\", with its present religious institutions, i.e., the Mosaic system, so designated from its primary external location\",\"\\\"Jerusalem that is above\\\", that is existing in heaven, according to the pattern of which the earthly Jerusalem was supposed to be built\",[\"metaphorically \\\"the City of God founded by Christ\\\", now wearing the form of the church, but after Christ\'s return to put on the form of the perfected Messianic kingdom\"],\"\\\"the heavenly Jerusalem\\\", that is the heavenly abode of God, Christ, the angels, saints of the Old and New Testament periods and those Christians that are alive at Christ\'s return\",\"\\\"the New Jerusalem\\\", a splendid visible city to be let down from heaven after the renovation of the world, the future abode of the blessed\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3389)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.rosˈo.ly.mɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.rowsˈow.lju.mɑ\",\"sbl\":\"hierosolyma\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-rose-OH-loo-ma\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-rose-OH-lyoo-ma\"},\"see\":[\"H3389\",\"G2419\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G2419.\"}', 'Jerusalem'),
(2415, 2415, 'Ἱεροσολυμίτης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a Hierosolymite, i.e., inhabitant of Hierosolyma\",\"long\":[\"a citizen or inhabitant of Jerusalem\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2414\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.ros.o.lyˈmi.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.rows.ow.ljuˈmi.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"hierosolymitēs\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-rose-oh-loo-MEE-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-rose-oh-lyoo-MEE-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2414\"]}', 'of Jerusalem'),
(2416, 2416, 'ἱεροσυλέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to be a temple-robber (figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to commit sacrilege, to rob a temple\",[\"in Romans 2:22, where the meaning is, \\\"thou who abhorrest idols and their contamination, doest yet not hesitate to plunder their shrines\\\"\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2417\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.ros.yˈlɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.rows.juˈle̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"hierosyleō\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-rose-oo-LEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-rose-yoo-LAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2417\"]}', 'commit sacrilege'),
(2417, 2417, 'ἱερόσυλος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a temple-despoiler\",\"long\":[\"guilty of sacrilege\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2411 and G4813\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛˈros.y.los\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞ˈrows.ju.lows\",\"sbl\":\"hierosylos\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-ROSE-oo-lose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-ROSE-yoo-lose\"},\"see\":[\"G2411\",\"G4813\"]}', 'robber of churches'),
(2418, 2418, 'ἱερουργέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to be a temple-worker, i.e., officiate as a priest (figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to minister in the manner of a priest, minister in priestly service\",[\"of those who defend the sanctity of the law by undergoing a violent death\",\"of the preaching of the gospel\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from a compound of G2411 and the base of G2041\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.rurˈɣɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.rurˈɣe̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"hierourgeō\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-roor-GEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-roor-GAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2041\",\"G2411\"]}', 'minister'),
(2419, 2419, 'Ἱερουσαλήμ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"set ye double peace\",\"short\":\"Hierusalem (i.e., Jerushalem), the capitol of Palestine\",\"long\":[\"denotes either the city itself or the inhabitants\",\"\\\"the Jerusalem that now is\\\", with its present religious institutions, i.e., the Mosaic system, so designated from its primary external location\",\"\\\"Jerusalem that is above\\\", that is existing in heaven, according to the pattern of which the earthly Jerusalem was supposed to be built\",[\"metaphorically \\\"the City of God founded by Christ\\\", now wearing the form of the church, but after Christ\'s return to put on the form of the perfected Messianic kingdom\"],\"\\\"the heavenly Jerusalem\\\", that is the heavenly abode of God, Christ, the angels, saints of the Old and New Testament periods and those Christians that are alive at Christ\'s return\",\"\\\"the New Jerusalem\\\", a splendid visible city to be let down from heaven after the renovation of the world, the future abode of the blessed\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3389)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.ru.sɑˈlem\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.ru.sɑˈle̞m\",\"sbl\":\"hierousalēm\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-roo-sa-LAME\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-roo-sa-LAME\"},\"see\":[\"H3389\",\"G2414\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G2414.\"}', 'Jerusalem');
INSERT INTO `lexicon_greek` (`id`, `strongs`, `word`, `data`, `usage`) VALUES
(2420, 2420, 'ἱερωσύνη', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"sacredness, i.e., (by implication) the priestly office\",\"long\":[\"priesthood, the priestly office\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2413\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.ɛ.roˈsy.ne\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.rowˈsju.ne̞\",\"sbl\":\"hierōsynē\",\"dic\":\"hee-eh-roh-SOO-nay\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-roh-SYOO-nay\"},\"see\":[\"G2413\"]}', 'priesthood'),
(2421, 2421, 'Ἰεσσαί', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"wealthy\",\"short\":\"Jessae (i.e., Jishai), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the father of David the king\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3448)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɛsˈsɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞sˈse\",\"sbl\":\"iessai\",\"dic\":\"ee-es-SEH\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ase-SAY\"},\"see\":[\"H3448\"]}', 'Jesse'),
(2422, 2422, 'Ἰεφθάε', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"whom God sets free\",\"short\":\"Jephthaë (i.e., Jiphtach), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"son of Gilead, and a judge in Israel\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3316)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɛˈfθɑ.ɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞ˈfθɑ.e̞\",\"sbl\":\"iephthae\",\"dic\":\"ee-eh-FTHA-eh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-FTHA-ay\"},\"see\":[\"H3316\"]}', 'Jephthah'),
(2423, 2423, 'Ἰεχονίας', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"whom Jehovah establishes\",\"short\":\"Jechonias (i.e., Jekonjah), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"was the son of Jehoiakim, and for three months and ten days king of Judah until Nebuchadnezzar carried him into captivity (597 BC)\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3204)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.ɛ.xoˈni.ɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞.xowˈni.ɑs\",\"sbl\":\"iechonias\",\"dic\":\"ee-eh-hoh-NEE-as\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-hoh-NEE-as\"},\"see\":[\"H3204\"]}', 'Jechonias'),
(2424, 2424, 'Ἰησοῦς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"Jehovah is salvation\",\"short\":\"Jesus (i.e., Jehoshua), the name of our Lord and two (three) other Israelites\",\"long\":[\"Joshua was the famous captain of the Israelites, Moses\' successor\",\"Jesus, son of Eliezer, one of the ancestors of Christ\",\"Jesus, the Son of God, the Saviour of mankind, God incarnate\",\"Jesus Barabbas was the captive robber whom the Jews begged Pilate to release instead of Christ\",\"Jesus, surnamed Justus, a Jewish Christian, an associate with Paul in the preaching of the gospel\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3091)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.eˈsus\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.e̞ˈsus\",\"sbl\":\"iēsous\",\"dic\":\"ee-ay-SOOS\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ay-SOOS\"},\"see\":[\"H3091\"]}', 'Jesus'),
(2425, 2425, 'ἱκανός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"competent (as if coming in season), i.e., ample (in amount) or fit (in character)\",\"long\":[\"sufficient\",[\"many enough, enough\",\"sufficient in ability, i.e., meet, fit\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from ἵκω (ἱκάνω or ἱκνέομαι, akin to G2240) (to arrive)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.kɑˈnos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.kɑˈnows\",\"sbl\":\"hikanos\",\"dic\":\"hee-ka-NOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ka-NOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2240\"]}', 'able, + content, enough, good, great, large, long (while), many, meet, much, security, sore, sufficient, worthy'),
(2426, 2426, 'ἱκανότης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"ability\",\"long\":[\"sufficient, ability or competency to do a thing\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2425\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.kɑˈno.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.kɑˈnow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"hikanotēs\",\"dic\":\"hee-ka-NOH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ka-NOH-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2425\"]}', 'sufficiency'),
(2427, 2427, 'ἱκανόω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to enable, i.e., qualify\",\"long\":[\"to make sufficient, render fit\",[\"to equip one with adequate power to perform duties of one\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2425\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.kɑˈno.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.kɑˈnow.ow\",\"sbl\":\"hikanoō\",\"dic\":\"hee-ka-NOH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ka-NOH-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2425\"]}', 'make able (meet)'),
(2428, 2428, 'ἱκετηρία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"intreaty\",\"long\":[\"an olive branch\",[\"for suppliants approached the one whose aid they would implore holding an olive branch entwined with white wool and fillets, to signify that they came as suppliants\"],\"supplication\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of the base of G2425 (through the idea of approaching for a favor)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.kɛ.teˈri.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ce̞.te̞ˈri.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"hiketēria\",\"dic\":\"hee-keh-tay-REE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-kay-tay-REE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2425\"]}', 'supplication'),
(2429, 2429, 'ἱκμάς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"dampness\",\"long\":[\"moisture\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hikˈmɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ikˈmɑs\",\"sbl\":\"hikmas\",\"dic\":\"heek-MAHS\",\"dic_mod\":\"eek-MAHS\"}}', 'moisture'),
(2430, 2430, 'Ἰκόνιον', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"little image\",\"short\":\"image-like; Iconium, a place in Asia Minor\",\"long\":[\"a famous city of Asia Minor, which was the capital of Lycaonia\"]},\"deriv\":\"perhaps from G1504\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈko.ni.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈkow.ni.own\",\"sbl\":\"ikonion\",\"dic\":\"ee-KOH-nee-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-KOH-nee-one\"},\"see\":[\"G1504\"]}', 'Iconium'),
(2431, 2431, 'ἱλαρός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"propitious or merry (\\\"hilarious\\\"), i.e., prompt or willing\",\"long\":[\"cheerful, joyous, prompt to do anything\"]},\"deriv\":\"from the same as G2436\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.lɑˈros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.lɑˈrows\",\"sbl\":\"hilaros\",\"dic\":\"hee-la-ROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-la-ROSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2436\"]}', 'cheerful'),
(2432, 2432, 'ἱλαρότης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"alacrity\",\"long\":[\"cheerfulness, readiness of mind\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2431\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.lɑˈro.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.lɑˈrow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"hilarotēs\",\"dic\":\"hee-la-ROH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-la-ROH-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2431\"]}', 'cheerfulness'),
(2433, 2433, 'ἱλάσκομαι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to conciliate, i.e., (transitively) to atone for (sin), or (intransitively) be propitious\",\"long\":[\"to render one\'s self, to appease, conciliate to one\'s self\",[\"to become propitious, be placated or appeased\",\"to be propitious, be gracious, be merciful\"],\"to expiate, make propitiation for\"]},\"deriv\":\"middle voice from the same as G2436\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hiˈlɑ.sko.mɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈlɑ.skow.me\",\"sbl\":\"hilaskomai\",\"dic\":\"hee-LA-skoh-meh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-LA-skoh-may\"},\"see\":[\"G2436\"]}', 'be merciful, make reconciliation for'),
(2434, 2434, 'ἱλασμός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"atonement, i.e., (concretely) an expiator\",\"long\":[\"an appeasing, propitiating\",\"the means of appeasing, a propitiation\"]},\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.lɑˈsmos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.lɑˈsmows\",\"sbl\":\"hilasmos\",\"dic\":\"hee-la-SMOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-la-SMOSE\"}}', 'propitiation'),
(2435, 2435, 'ἱλαστήριον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"an expiatory (place or thing), i.e., (concretely) an atoning victim, or (specially) the lid of the Ark (in the Temple)\",\"long\":[\"relating to an appeasing or expiating, having placating or expiating force, expiatory; a means of appeasing or expiating, a propitiation\",[\"used of the cover of the ark of the covenant in the Holy of Holies, which was sprinkled with the blood of the expiatory victim on the annual day of atonement (this rite signifying that the life of the people, the loss of which they had merited by their sins, was offered to God in the blood as the life of the victim, and that God by this ceremony was appeased and their sins expiated); hence the lid of expiation, the propitiatory\",\"an expiatory sacrifice\",\"a expiatory victim\"]]},\"deriv\":\"neuter of a derivative of G2433\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.lɑˈste.ri.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.lɑˈste̞.ri.own\",\"sbl\":\"hilastērion\",\"dic\":\"hee-la-STAY-ree-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-la-STAY-ree-one\"},\"see\":[\"G2433\"]}', 'mercyseat, propitiation'),
(2436, 2436, 'ἵλεως', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"cheerful (as attractive), i.e., propitious; adverbially (by Hebraism) God be gracious!, i.e., (in averting some calamity) far be it\",\"long\":[\"propitious, merciful\"]},\"deriv\":\"perhaps from the alternate form of G0138\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈhi.lɛ.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.le̞.ows\",\"sbl\":\"hileōs\",\"dic\":\"HEE-leh-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-lay-ose\"},\"see\":[\"G0138\"]}', 'be it far, merciful'),
(2437, 2437, 'Ἰλλυρικόν', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"the lyric band\",\"short\":\"(the) Illyrican (shore), i.e., (as a name itself) Illyricum, a region of Europe\",\"long\":[\"a region lying between Italy, Germany, Macedonia and Thrice, having on one side the Adriatic Sea, and on the other the Danube\"]},\"deriv\":\"neuter of an adjective from a name of uncertain derivation\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"il.ly.riˈkon\",\"ipa_mod\":\"il.lju.riˈkown\",\"sbl\":\"illyrikon\",\"dic\":\"eel-loo-ree-KONE\",\"dic_mod\":\"eel-lyoo-ree-KONE\"}}', 'Illyricum'),
(2438, 2438, 'ἱμάς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a strap, i.e., (specially) the tie (of a sandal) or the lash (of a scourge)\",\"long\":[\"a thong of leather, a strap\",[\"in the New Testament of the thongs with which captives or criminals were either bound or beaten\",\"of the thongs or ties by which sandals were fastened to the feet\"]]},\"deriv\":\"perhaps from the same as G0260\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hiˈmɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈmɑs\",\"sbl\":\"himas\",\"dic\":\"hee-MAHS\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-MAHS\"},\"see\":[\"G0260\"]}', 'latchet, thong'),
(2439, 2439, 'ἱματίζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to dress\",\"long\":[\"to clothe\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2440\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.mɑˈti.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.mɑˈti.zow\",\"sbl\":\"himatizō\",\"dic\":\"hee-ma-TEE-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ma-TEE-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2440\"]}', 'clothe'),
(2440, 2440, 'ἱμάτιον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a dress (inner or outer)\",\"long\":[\"a garment (of any sort)\",[\"garments, i.e., the cloak or mantle and the tunic\"],\"the upper garment, the cloak or mantle\"]},\"deriv\":\"neuter of a presumed derivative of ennumi (to put on)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hiˈmɑ.ti.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈmɑ.ti.own\",\"sbl\":\"himation\",\"dic\":\"hee-MA-tee-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-MA-tee-one\"}}', 'apparel, cloke, clothes, garment, raiment, robe, vesture'),
(2441, 2441, 'ἱματισμός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"clothing\",\"long\":[\"clothing, apparel\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2439\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.mɑ.tiˈsmos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.mɑ.tiˈsmows\",\"sbl\":\"himatismos\",\"dic\":\"hee-ma-tee-SMOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ma-tee-SMOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2439\"]}', 'apparel (X -led), array, raiment, vesture'),
(2442, 2442, 'ἱμείρομαι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"of uncertain affinity); to long for\",\"long\":[\"to desire, long for, especially the longing of love\"]},\"deriv\":\"middle voice from ἵμερος (a yearning\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hiˈmi.ro.mɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈmi.row.me\",\"sbl\":\"himeiromai\",\"dic\":\"hee-MEE-roh-meh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-MEE-roh-may\"}}', 'be affectionately desirous'),
(2443, 2443, 'ἵνα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"in order that (denoting the purpose or the result)\",\"long\":[\"that, in order that, so that\"]},\"deriv\":\"probably from the same as the former part of G1438 (through the demonstrative idea; compare G3588)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈhi.nɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.nɑ\",\"sbl\":\"hina\",\"dic\":\"HEE-na\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-na\"},\"see\":[\"G1438\",\"G3363\",\"G3588\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G3363.\"}', 'albeit, because, to the intent (that), lest, so as, (so) that, (for) to'),
(2444, 2444, 'ἱνατί', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"for what reason ?, i.e., why?\",\"long\":[\"for what purpose, wherefore, why\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2443 and G5101\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.nɑˈti\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.nɑˈti\",\"sbl\":\"hinati\",\"dic\":\"hee-na-TEE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-na-TEE\"},\"see\":[\"G2443\",\"G5101\"]}', 'wherefore, why'),
(2445, 2445, 'Ἰόππη', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"beautiful\",\"short\":\"Joppe (i.e., Japho), a place in Palestine\",\"long\":[\"Joppa, a city of Palestine on the Mediterranean, lying on the border of the tribes of Dan and Ephraim\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3305)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈop.pe\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈowp.pe̞\",\"sbl\":\"ioppē\",\"dic\":\"ee-OPE-pay\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-OPE-pay\"},\"see\":[\"H3305\"],\"comment\":\"It was subject to the Jews from the times of the Maccabees. It had a famous but dangerous port and carried on a flourishing trade. It is now called Jaffa.\"}', 'Joppa'),
(2446, 2446, 'Ἰορδάνης', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"the descender\",\"short\":\"the Jordanes (i.e., Jarden), a river of Palestine\",\"long\":[\"the one river of Palestine, has its course of little more than 200 miles (300 km), from the roots of Anti-Lebanon to the head of the Dead Sea\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3383)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.orˈðɑ.nes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owrˈðɑ.ne̞s\",\"sbl\":\"iordanēs\",\"dic\":\"ee-ore-THA-nase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ore-THA-nase\"},\"see\":[\"H3383\"]}', 'Jordan'),
(2447, 2447, 'ἰός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"rust (as if emitted by metals); also venom (as emitted by serpents)\",\"long\":[\"poison (of animals)\",[\"poison of asps is under their lips,\",\"spoken of men given to reviling and calumniating and thereby injuring others\"],\"rust\"]},\"deriv\":\"perhaps from εἶμι (to go) or ἵημι (to send)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈows\",\"sbl\":\"ios\",\"dic\":\"ee-OSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-OSE\"}}', 'poison, rust'),
(2448, 2448, 'Ἰουδά', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"he shall be praised\",\"short\":\"Judah (i.e., Jehudah or Juttah), a part of (or place in) Palestine\",\"long\":[\"the fourth son of the patriarch Jacob\",\"the tribe that were the offspring of Judah\",\"the region occupied by the tribe\",\"a city of the tribe of Judah, conjectured to be Hebron, which was a city assigned to the priests and located in the hill country, and the native place of John the Baptist according to Jewish tradition\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3063 or perhaps H3194)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.uˈðɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.uˈðɑ\",\"sbl\":\"iouda\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-THA\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-THA\"},\"see\":[\"H3063\",\"H3194\"]}', 'Judah'),
(2449, 2449, 'Ἰουδαία', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"he shall be praised\",\"short\":\"the Judaean land (i.e., Judaea), a region of Palestine\",\"long\":[\"in a narrower sense, to the southern portion of Palestine lying on this side of the Jordan and the Dead Sea, to distinguish it from Samaria, Galilee, Peraea, and Idumaea\",\"in a broader sense, referring to all Palestine\"]},\"deriv\":\"feminine of G2453 (with G1093 implied)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.uˈðɛ.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.uˈðe.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"ioudaia\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-THEH-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-THAY-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G1093\",\"G2453\"]}', 'Judaea'),
(2450, 2450, 'Ἰουδαΐζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to become a Judaean, i.e., \\\"Judaize\\\"\",\"long\":[\"to adopt Jewish customs and rites, imitate the Jews, Judaise\",[\"one who observes the ritual law of the Jews\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2453\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.u.ðɑˈi.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.u.ðɑˈi.zow\",\"sbl\":\"ioudaizō\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-tha-EE-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-tha-EE-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2453\"]}', 'live as the Jews'),
(2451, 2451, 'Ἰουδαϊκός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"Judaïc, i.e., resembling a Judaean\",\"long\":[\"Jewish\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2453\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.u.ðɑ.iˈkos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.u.ðɑ.iˈkows\",\"sbl\":\"ioudaikos\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-tha-ee-KOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-tha-ee-KOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2453\"]}', 'Jewish'),
(2452, 2452, 'Ἰουδαϊκῶς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"Judaïcally or in a manner resembling a Judaean\",\"long\":[\"Jewishly, after the manner of the Jews\"]},\"deriv\":\"adverb from G2451\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.u.ðɑ.iˈkos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.u.ðɑ.iˈkows\",\"sbl\":\"ioudaikōs\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-tha-ee-KOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-tha-ee-KOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2451\"]}', 'as do the Jews'),
(2453, 2453, 'Ἰουδαῖος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"Judaean, i.e., belonging to Jehudah\",\"long\":[\"Jewish, belonging to the Jewish race\",\"Jewish as respects to birth, race, religion\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2448 (in the sense of G2455 as a country)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.uˈðɛ.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.uˈðe.ows\",\"sbl\":\"ioudaios\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-THEH-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-THAY-ose\"},\"see\":[\"G2448\",\"G2455\"]}', 'Jew(-ess), of Judaea'),
(2454, 2454, 'Ἰουδαϊσμός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"\\\"Judaism\\\", i.e., the Jewish faith and usages\",\"long\":[\"the Jewish faith and worship, religion of the Jews, Judaism\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2450\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.u.ðɑ.iˈsmos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.u.ðɑ.iˈsmows\",\"sbl\":\"ioudaismos\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-tha-ee-SMOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-tha-ee-SMOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2450\"]}', 'Jews\' religion'),
(2455, 2455, 'Ἰούδας', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"he shall be praised\",\"short\":\"Judas (i.e., Jehudah), the name of ten Israelites; also of the posterity of one of them and its region\",\"long\":[\"the fourth son of Jacob\",\"an unknown ancestor of Christ\",\"a man surnamed the Galilean, who at the time of the census of Quirinus, excited the revolt in Galilee (see Acts 5:37)\",\"a certain Jew of Damascus (see Acts 9:11)\",\"a prophet surnamed Barsabas, of the church at Jerusalem (see Acts 15:22, 27, 32)\",\"the apostle who was surnamed Lebbaeus or Thaddaeus (see John 14:22), and believed to have written the Epistle of Jude\",\"the half-brother of Jesus (see Matthew 13:55)\",\"Judas Iscariot, the apostle who betrayed Jesus\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3063)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈu.ðɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈu.ðɑs\",\"sbl\":\"ioudas\",\"dic\":\"ee-OO-thahs\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-OO-thahs\"},\"see\":[\"H3063\"]}', 'Juda(-h, -s); Jude'),
(2456, 2456, 'Ἰουλία', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"soft haired\",\"short\":\"Julia, a Christian woman\",\"long\":[\"a Christian woman\"]},\"deriv\":\"feminine of the same as G2457\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.uˈli.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.uˈli.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"ioulia\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-LEE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-LEE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2457\"]}', 'Julia'),
(2457, 2457, 'Ἰούλιος', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"soft-haired\",\"short\":\"Julius, a centurion\",\"long\":[\"the centurion of \\\"Augustus Band\\\", to whose charge Paul was delivered when he was sent prisoner from Caesarea to Rome\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Latin origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈu.li.os\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈu.li.ows\",\"sbl\":\"ioulios\",\"dic\":\"ee-OO-lee-ose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-OO-lee-ose\"}}', 'Julius'),
(2458, 2458, 'Ἰουνιᾶς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"youthful\",\"short\":\"Junias, a Christian\",\"long\":[\"a Christian woman at Rome, mentioned by Paul as one of his kinsfolk and fellow prisoners\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Latin origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.u.niˈɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.u.niˈɑs\",\"sbl\":\"iounias\",\"dic\":\"ee-oo-nee-AS\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oo-nee-AS\"}}', 'Junias'),
(2459, 2459, 'Ἰοῦστος', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"just\",\"short\":\"Justus, the name of three Christian\",\"long\":[\"a surname of Joseph, called Barsabas (see Acts 1:23)\",\"of Titus, a Christian at Corinth, with whom Paul lodged (see Acts 18:7)\",\"a surname of Jesus, a friend of Paul (see Colossians 4:11)\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Latin origin (\\\"just\\\")\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈu.stos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈu.stows\",\"sbl\":\"ioustos\",\"dic\":\"ee-OO-stose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-OO-stose\"}}', 'Justus'),
(2460, 2460, 'ἱππεύς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"an equestrian, i.e., member of a cavalry corps\",\"long\":[\"a horseman\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2462\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hipˈpɛβs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ipˈpefs\",\"sbl\":\"hippeus\",\"dic\":\"heep-PEVS\",\"dic_mod\":\"eep-PAYFS\"},\"see\":[\"G2462\"]}', 'horseman'),
(2461, 2461, 'ἱππικόν', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"the cavalry force\",\"long\":[\"equestrian, the horse(men), cavalry\"]},\"deriv\":\"neuter of a derivative of G2462\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hip.piˈkon\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ip.piˈkown\",\"sbl\":\"hippikon\",\"dic\":\"heep-pee-KONE\",\"dic_mod\":\"eep-pee-KONE\"},\"see\":[\"G2462\"]}', 'horse(-men)'),
(2462, 2462, 'ἵππος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a horse\",\"long\":[\"a horse\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈhip.pos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈip.pows\",\"sbl\":\"hippos\",\"dic\":\"HEEP-pose\",\"dic_mod\":\"EEP-pose\"}}', 'horse'),
(2463, 2463, 'ἶρις', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a rainbow (\\\"iris\\\")\",\"long\":[\"a rainbow\"]},\"deriv\":\"perhaps from G2046 (as a symbol of the female messenger of the pagan deities)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.ris\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.ris\",\"sbl\":\"iris\",\"dic\":\"EE-rees\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-rees\"},\"see\":[\"G2046\"]}', 'rainbow'),
(2464, 2464, 'Ἰσαάκ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"to laugh\",\"short\":\"Isaac (i.e., Jitschak), the son of Abraham\",\"long\":[\"the son of Abraham and Sarah\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3327)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.sɑˈɑk\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.sɑˈɑk\",\"sbl\":\"isaak\",\"dic\":\"ee-sa-AK\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-sa-AK\"},\"see\":[\"H3327\"]}', 'Isaac'),
(2465, 2465, 'ἰσάγγελος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"like an angel, i.e., angelic\",\"long\":[\"like the angels\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2470 and G0032\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈsɑŋ.ɣɛ.los\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈsɑŋ.ʝe̞.lows\",\"sbl\":\"isangelos\",\"dic\":\"ee-SAHNG-geh-lose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-SAHNG-gay-lose\"},\"see\":[\"G0032\",\"G2470\"]}', 'equal unto the angels'),
(2466, 2466, 'Ἰσαχάρ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"reward\",\"short\":\"Isachar (i.e., Jissaskar), a son of Jacob (figuratively, his descendant)\",\"long\":[\"the ninth son of Jacob and the fifth of Leah\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3485)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.sɑˈxɑr\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.sɑˈxɑr\",\"sbl\":\"isachar\",\"dic\":\"ee-sa-HAHR\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-sa-HAHR\"},\"see\":[\"H3485\"]}', 'Issachar'),
(2467, 2467, 'ἴσημι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to know\",\"long\":[\"to know\"]},\"deriv\":\"assumed by some as the base of certain irregular forms of G1492\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.se.mi\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.se̞.mi\",\"sbl\":\"isēmi\",\"dic\":\"EE-say-mee\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-say-mee\"},\"see\":[\"G1492\"]}', 'know'),
(2468, 2468, 'ἴσθι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"be thou\",\"long\":[\"be thou\"]},\"deriv\":\"second person imperative present of G1510\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.sθi\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.sθi\",\"sbl\":\"isthi\",\"dic\":\"EE-sthee\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-sthee\"},\"see\":[\"G1510\"]}', '+ agree, be, X give thyself wholly to'),
(2469, 2469, 'Ἰσκαριώτης', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"men of Kerioth\",\"short\":\"inhabitant of Kerioth; Iscariotes (i.e., Keriothite), an epithet of Judas the traitor\",\"long\":[\"the apostle who betrayed Jesus\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (probably H0377 and H7149)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.skɑ.riˈo.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.skɑ.riˈow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"iskariōtēs\",\"dic\":\"ee-ska-ree-OH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ska-ree-OH-tase\"},\"see\":[\"H0377\",\"H7149\"]}', 'Iscariot'),
(2470, 2470, 'ἴσος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"similar (in amount and kind)\",\"long\":[\"equal, in quantity or quality\"]},\"deriv\":\"probably from G1492 (through the idea of seeming)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.sos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.sows\",\"sbl\":\"isos\",\"dic\":\"EE-sose\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-sose\"},\"see\":[\"G1492\"]}', '+ agree, as much, equal, like'),
(2471, 2471, 'ἰσότης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"likeness (in condition or proportion); by implication, equity\",\"long\":[\"equality\",\"equity, fairness, what is equitable\"]},\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈso.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈsow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"isotēs\",\"dic\":\"ee-SOH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-SOH-tase\"}}', 'equal(-ity)'),
(2472, 2472, 'ἰσότιμος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"of equal value or honor\",\"long\":[\"equally precious\",\"equally honored, to be esteemed equal to\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2470 and G5092\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈso.ti.mos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈsow.ti.mows\",\"sbl\":\"isotimos\",\"dic\":\"ee-SOH-tee-mose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-SOH-tee-mose\"},\"see\":[\"G2470\",\"G5092\"]}', 'like precious'),
(2473, 2473, 'ἰσόψυχος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"of similar spirit\",\"long\":[\"equal in soul\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2470 and G5590\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈso.p͡sy.xos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈsow.p͡sju.xows\",\"sbl\":\"isopsychos\",\"dic\":\"ee-SOH-psoo-hose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-SOH-psyoo-hose\"},\"see\":[\"G2470\",\"G5590\"]}', 'likeminded'),
(2474, 2474, 'Ἰσραήλ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"he shall be a prince of God\",\"short\":\"Israel (i.e., Jisrael), the adopted name of Jacob, including his descendants (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"the name given to the patriarch Jacob (and borne by him in addition to his former name)\",\"the family or descendants of Israel, the race of Israel\",\"Christians, the Israel of God (Galatians 6:16), for not all those who draw their bodily descent from Israel are true Israelites, i.e., are those whom God pronounces to be Israelites and has chosen to salvation\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3478)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"is.rɑˈel\",\"ipa_mod\":\"is.rɑˈe̞l\",\"sbl\":\"israēl\",\"dic\":\"ees-ra-ALE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ees-ra-ALE\"},\"see\":[\"H3478\"]}', 'Israel'),
(2475, 2475, 'Ἰσραηλίτης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"an \\\"Israelite\\\", i.e., descendant of Israel (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"an Israelite, one of the race of Israel, a name to be held in honor\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2474\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"is.rɑ.eˈli.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"is.rɑ.e̞ˈli.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"israēlitēs\",\"dic\":\"ees-ra-ay-LEE-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ees-ra-ay-LEE-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2474\"]}', 'Israelite'),
(2476, 2476, 'ἵστημι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to stand (transitively or intransitively), used in various applications (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to cause or make to stand, to place, put, set\",[\"to bid to stand by, [set up]\",[\"in the presence of others, in the midst, before judges, before members of the Sanhedrin;\",\"to place\"],\"to make firm, fix establish\",[\"to cause a person or a thing to keep his or its place\",\"to stand, be kept intact (of family, a kingdom), to escape in safety\",\"to establish a thing, cause it to stand\",[\"to uphold or sustain the authority or force of anything\"]],\"to set or place in a balance\",[\"to weigh: money to one (because in very early times before the introduction of coinage, the metals used to be weighed)\"]],\"to stand\",[\"to stand by or near\",[\"to stop, stand still, to stand immovable, stand firm\",[\"of the foundation of a building\"]],\"to stand\",[\"continue safe and sound, stand unharmed, to stand ready or prepared\",\"to be of a steadfast mind\",\"of quality, one who does not hesitate, does not waiver\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"a prolonged form of a primary στάω <pronunciation strongs=\\\"stah\'-o\\\"/> (of the same meaning, and used for it in certain tenses)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈhi.ste.mi\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.ste̞.mi\",\"sbl\":\"histēmi\",\"dic\":\"HEE-stay-mee\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-stay-mee\"},\"see\":[\"G5087\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G5087.\"}', 'abide, appoint, bring, continue, covenant, establish, hold up, lay, present, set (up), stanch, stand (by, forth, still, up)'),
(2477, 2477, 'ἱστορέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to be knowing (learned), i.e., (by implication) to visit for information (interview)\",\"long\":[\"to enquire into, examine, investigate\",\"to find out, learn, by enquiry\",\"to gain knowledge of by visiting\",[\"of some distinguished person, to become personally acquainted with, know face to face\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of G1492\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"hi.stoˈrɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.stowˈre̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"historeō\",\"dic\":\"hee-stoh-REH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-stoh-RAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G1492\"]}', 'see'),
(2478, 2478, 'ἰσχυρός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"forcible (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"strong, mighty\",[\"of living beings\",[\"strong either in body or in mind\",\"of one who has strength of soul to sustain the attacks of Satan, strong and therefore exhibiting many excellences\"],\"on inanimate things\",[\"strong, violent, forcibly uttered, firm, sure\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2479\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.sxyˈros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.sçjuˈrows\",\"sbl\":\"ischyros\",\"dic\":\"ee-skoo-ROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-skyoo-ROSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2479\"]}', 'boisterous, mighty(-ier), powerful, strong(-er) (man), valiant'),
(2479, 2479, 'ἰσχύς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"compare ἔσχον, a form of G2192); forcefulness (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"ability, force, strength, might\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a derivative of ἰς (force\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈsxys\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈsxjus\",\"sbl\":\"ischys\",\"dic\":\"ee-SKOOS\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-SKYOOS\"},\"see\":[\"G2192\"]}', 'ability, might(-ily), power, strength'),
(2480, 2480, 'ἰσχύω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to have (or exercise) force (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to be strong\",[\"to be strong in body, to be robust, to be in sound health\"],\"to have power\",[\"to have power as shown by extraordinary deeds\",[\"to exert, wield power, to have strength to overcome\"],\"to be a force, avail\",\"to be serviceable\",\"to be able, can\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2479\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈsxy.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈsxju.ow\",\"sbl\":\"ischyō\",\"dic\":\"ee-SKOO-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-SKYOO-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2479\"]}', 'be able, avail, can do(-not), could, be good, might, prevail, be of strength, be whole, + much work'),
(2481, 2481, 'ἴσως', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"likely, i.e., perhaps\",\"long\":[\"equally, in like manner\",\"agreeably to expectation, i.e., it may be, probably\"]},\"deriv\":\"adverb from G2470\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.sos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.sows\",\"sbl\":\"isōs\",\"dic\":\"EE-sose\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-sose\"},\"see\":[\"G2470\"]}', 'it may be'),
(2482, 2482, 'Ἰταλία', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"calf like\",\"short\":\"Italia, a region of Europe\",\"long\":[\"the whole peninsula between the Alps and the Straits of Messina\"]},\"deriv\":\"probably of foreign origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.tɑˈli.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.tɑˈli.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"italia\",\"dic\":\"ee-ta-LEE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ta-LEE-ah\"}}', 'Italy'),
(2483, 2483, 'Ἰταλικός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"Italic, i.e., belonging to Italia\",\"long\":[\"Italian\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2482\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.tɑ.liˈkos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.tɑ.liˈkows\",\"sbl\":\"italikos\",\"dic\":\"ee-ta-lee-KOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-ta-lee-KOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2482\"]}', 'Italian'),
(2484, 2484, 'Ἰτουραΐα', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"past the limits, he will arrange\",\"short\":\"Ituraea (i.e., Jetur), a region of Palestine\",\"long\":[\"a mountainous region, lying northeast of Palestine and west of Damascus\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3195)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.tu.rɑˈi.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.tu.rɑˈi.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"itouraia\",\"dic\":\"ee-too-ra-EE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-too-ra-EE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"H3195\"],\"comment\":\"At the time when John the Baptist made his public appearance, Ituraea was subject to Philip the tetrarch, son of Herod the Great, among the regions assigned to this prince after his father\'s death. It was brought under Jewish control by king Aristobulus around 100 BC. Its inhabitants have been noted for robbery and skillful use of the bow.\"}', 'Ituraea'),
(2485, 2485, 'ἰχθύδιον', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a petty fish\",\"long\":[\"a little fish\"]},\"deriv\":\"diminutive from G2486\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ixˈθy.ði.on\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ixˈθju.ði.own\",\"sbl\":\"ichthydion\",\"dic\":\"eek-THOO-thee-one\",\"dic_mod\":\"eek-THYOO-thee-one\"},\"see\":[\"G2486\"]}', 'little (small) fish'),
(2486, 2486, 'ἰχθύς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a fish\",\"long\":[\"a fish\"]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ixˈθys\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ixˈθjus\",\"sbl\":\"ichthys\",\"dic\":\"eek-THOOS\",\"dic_mod\":\"eek-THYOOS\"}}', 'fish'),
(2487, 2487, 'ἴχνος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a track (figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"a footprint, track, footstep\",\"in the New Testament, metaphorically of imitating the example of any one\"]},\"deriv\":\"from ἰκνέομαι (to arrive; compare G2240)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈi.xnos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈi.xnows\",\"sbl\":\"ichnos\",\"dic\":\"EE-hnose\",\"dic_mod\":\"EE-hnose\"},\"see\":[\"G2240\"]}', 'step'),
(2488, 2488, 'Ἰωάθαμ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"Jehovah is upright\",\"short\":\"Joatham (i.e., Jotham), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the son of King Uzziah or Azariah and Jerusha\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3147)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈɑ.θɑm\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈɑ.θɑm\",\"sbl\":\"iōatham\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-AH-thahm\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-AH-thahm\"},\"see\":[\"H3147\"]}', 'Joatham'),
(2489, 2489, 'Ἰωάννα', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"Jehovah is a gracious giver\",\"short\":\"Joanna, a Christian\",\"long\":[\"the wife of Chuza, Herod\'s steward, and a follower of Jesus\"]},\"deriv\":\"feminine of the same as G2491\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈɑn.nɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈɑn.nɑ\",\"sbl\":\"iōanna\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-AN-na\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-AN-na\"},\"see\":[\"G2491\"]}', 'Joanna'),
(2490, 2490, 'Ἰωαννᾶς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"grace, gift of God\",\"short\":\"Joannas, an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"one of the ancestors of Christ\"]},\"deriv\":\"a form of G2491\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.o.ɑnˈnɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ow.ɑnˈnɑs\",\"sbl\":\"iōannas\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-an-NAHS\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-an-NAHS\"},\"see\":[\"G2491\"]}', 'Joannas'),
(2491, 2491, 'Ἰωάννης', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"Jehovah is a gracious giver\",\"short\":\"Joannes (i.e., Jochanan), the name of four Israelites\",\"long\":[\"John the Baptist, the son of Zacharias and Elisabeth, the forerunner of Christ\",\"John the apostle, the writer of the 4th Gospel, son of Zebedee and Salome, brother of James the elder, the writer of the three epistles of John and the book of Revelation, perhaps referred to as the one \\\"whom Jesus loved\\\" in the Gospel of John\",\"John, surnamed Mark, the companion of Barnabas and Paul (see Acts 12:12)\",\"John, a certain man, a member of the Sanhedrin (see Acts 5:6)\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3110)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈɑn.nes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈɑn.ne̞s\",\"sbl\":\"iōannēs\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-AN-nase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-AN-nase\"},\"see\":[\"H3110\"]}', 'John'),
(2492, 2492, 'Ἰώβ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"the cry of woe, I will exclaim\",\"short\":\"Job, a patriarch\",\"long\":[\"Job, a man known for his piety and, consistency and fortitude in the endurance of trials\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H0347)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈoβ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈowv\",\"sbl\":\"iōb\",\"dic\":\"ee-OVE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-OVE\"},\"see\":[\"H0347\"],\"comment\":\"His experiences are related in the Old Testament book of Job.\"}', 'Job'),
(2493, 2493, 'Ἰωήλ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"to whom Jehovah is God\",\"short\":\"Joel, an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the second of the twelve minor prophets, the son of Pethuel, probably prophesied in Judah in the reign of Uzziah\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3100)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈel\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈe̞l\",\"sbl\":\"iōēl\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-ALE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-ALE\"},\"see\":[\"H3100\"]}', 'Joel'),
(2494, 2494, 'Ἰωνάν', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"Jehovah is a gracious giver\",\"short\":\"Jonan, an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"one of the ancestors of Christ\"]},\"deriv\":\"probably for G2491 or G2495\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈnɑn\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈnɑn\",\"sbl\":\"iōnan\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-NAHN\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-NAHN\"},\"see\":[\"G2491\",\"G2495\"]}', 'Jonan'),
(2495, 2495, 'Ἰωνᾶς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"dove\",\"short\":\"Jonas (i.e., Jonah), the name of two Israelites\",\"long\":[\"the fifth minor prophet, the son of Amittai, and a native of Gath-hepher and lived during the reign of Jeroboam II, king of Israel\",\"Jonas, the father of Peter\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3124)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈnɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈnɑs\",\"sbl\":\"iōnas\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-NAHS\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-NAHS\"},\"see\":[\"H3124\"]}', 'Jonas'),
(2496, 2496, 'Ἰωράμ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"whom Jehovah has exalted\",\"short\":\"Joram, an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah, succeeded his father on the throne of Judah\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3141)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈrɑm\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈrɑm\",\"sbl\":\"iōram\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-RAHM\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-RAHM\"},\"see\":[\"H3141\"]}', 'Joram'),
(2497, 2497, 'Ἰωρείμ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"whom Jehovah has exalted\",\"short\":\"Jorim, an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the son of Matthat, in the genealogy of Christ\"]},\"deriv\":\"perhaps for G2496\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈrim\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈrim\",\"sbl\":\"iōreim\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-REEM\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-REEM\"},\"see\":[\"G2496\"]}', 'Jorim'),
(2498, 2498, 'Ἰωσαφάτ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"whom Jehovah judges\",\"short\":\"Josaphat (i.e., Jehoshaphat), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the king of Judah, son of Asa\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3092)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.o.sɑˈfɑt\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.ow.sɑˈfɑt\",\"sbl\":\"iōsaphat\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-sa-FAHT\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-sa-FAHT\"},\"see\":[\"H3092\"]}', 'Josaphat'),
(2499, 2499, 'Ἰωσή', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"he will be sustained of Jehovah\",\"short\":\"Jose, an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"the son of Eliezer, in the genealogy of Jesus Christ\"]},\"deriv\":\"genitive case of G2500\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈse\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈse̞\",\"sbl\":\"iōsē\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-SAY\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-SAY\"},\"see\":[\"G2500\"]}', 'Jose'),
(2500, 2500, 'Ἰωσῆς', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"exalted\",\"short\":\"Joses, the name of two Israelites\",\"long\":[\"one of the ancestors of Christ, Luke 3:29\",\"Joses, the brother of Jesus, Mark 6:3\",\"Joses, the son of Mary, the sister of the mother of Jesus, Matthew 27:56\",\"Joses, a Levite, Acts 4:36\"]},\"deriv\":\"perhaps for G2501\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈses\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈse̞s\",\"sbl\":\"iōsēs\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-SASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-SASE\"},\"see\":[\"G2499\",\"G2501\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G2499.\"}', 'Joses'),
(2501, 2501, 'Ἰωσήφ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"let Him (God) add, increaser\",\"short\":\"Joseph, the name of seven Israelites\",\"long\":[\"the patriarch, the eleventh son of Jacob\",\"the son of Jonan or Jonam, one of the ancestors of Christ (see Luke 3:30)\",\"the son of Judah (also spelled Judas or Joda) another ancestor of Jesus (see Luke 3:26)\",\"the son of Mattathias, another ancestor of Christ (see Luke 3:24)\",\"the husband of Mary, the mother of Jesus\",\"a half-brother of Jesus (see Matthew 13:55)\",\"Joseph of Arimathaea, a member of the Sanhedrin, who believed in Jesus (see Matthew 27:57, 59; Mark 15:43, 45)\",\"Joseph surnamed Barnabas (see Acts 4:36)\",\"Joseph call Barsabas and surnamed Justus (see Acts 1:23)\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H3130)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈsef\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈse̞f\",\"sbl\":\"iōsēph\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-SAFE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-SAFE\"},\"see\":[\"H3130\"]}', 'Joseph'),
(2502, 2502, 'Ἰωσίας', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"whom Jehovah heals\",\"short\":\"Josias (i.e., Joshiah), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"king of Judah, who restored among the Jews the worship of the true God, and after a reign of thirty one years was slain in battle about 611 BC\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H2977)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"i.oˈsi.ɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"i.owˈsi.ɑs\",\"sbl\":\"iōsias\",\"dic\":\"ee-oh-SEE-as\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-oh-SEE-as\"},\"see\":[\"H2977\"]}', 'Josias'),
(2503, 2503, 'ἰῶτα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"\\\"iota\\\", the name of the eighth letter of the Greek alphabet, put (figuratively) for a very small part of anything\",\"long\":[\"the Hebrew letter Yod (י), the smallest of them all\",[\"hence equivalent to the minutest part\"]]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (the tenth letter of the Hebrew alphabet)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"iˈo.tɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"iˈow.tɑ\",\"sbl\":\"iōta\",\"dic\":\"ee-OH-ta\",\"dic_mod\":\"ee-OH-ta\"}}', 'jot'),
(2504, 2504, 'κἀγώ', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"so also the dative case κἀμοί <pronunciation strongs=\\\"kam-oy\'\\\"/>, and accusative case κἀμέ <pronunciation strongs=\\\"kam-eh\'\\\"/> and (or also, even, etc.) I, (to) me\",\"long\":[\"and I\",\"I also, I as well, I likewise, in like manner I\",\"even I, this selfsame I\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2532 and G1473\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈɣo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈɣow\",\"sbl\":\"kagō\",\"dic\":\"ka-GOH\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-GOH\"},\"see\":[\"G1473\",\"G2532\"]}', '(and, even, even so, so) I (also, in like wise), both me, me also'),
(2505, 2505, 'καθά', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"according to which things, i.e., just as\",\"long\":[\"according as, just as\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and the neuter plural of G3739\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθɑ\",\"sbl\":\"katha\",\"dic\":\"ka-THA\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THA\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\",\"G3739\"]}', 'as'),
(2506, 2506, 'καθαίρεσις', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"demolition; figuratively, extinction\",\"long\":[\"a pulling down, destruction, demolition\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2507\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθɛ.rɛ.sis\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθe.re̞.sis\",\"sbl\":\"kathairesis\",\"dic\":\"ka-THEH-reh-sees\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THAY-ray-sees\"},\"see\":[\"G2507\"]}', 'destruction, pulling down'),
(2507, 2507, 'καθαιρέω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to lower (or with violence) demolish (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to take down\",[\"without the notion of violence: to detach from the cross, one crucified\",\"with the use of force: to throw down, cast down\"],\"to pull down, demolish\",[\"the subtle reasonings (of opponents) likened to a fortress, i.e., to refute, to destroy\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G0138 (including its alternate)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θɛˈrɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θeˈre̞.ow\",\"sbl\":\"kathaireō\",\"dic\":\"ka-theh-REH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-thay-RAY-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G0138\",\"G2596\"]}', 'cast (pull, put, take) down, destroy'),
(2508, 2508, 'καθαίρω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to cleanse, i.e., (specially) to prune; figuratively, to expiate\",\"long\":[\"to cleanse, of filth impurity, etc\",[\"to prune trees and vines from useless shoots\",\"metaphorically from guilt, to expiate\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2513\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθɛ.ro\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθe.row\",\"sbl\":\"kathairō\",\"dic\":\"ka-THEH-roh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THAY-roh\"},\"see\":[\"G2513\"]}', 'purge'),
(2509, 2509, 'καθάπερ', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"exactly as\",\"long\":[\"according as, just as, even as\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2505 and G4007\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθɑ.pɛr\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθɑ.pe̞r\",\"sbl\":\"kathaper\",\"dic\":\"ka-THA-per\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THA-pare\"},\"see\":[\"G2505\",\"G4007\"]}', '(even, as well) as'),
(2510, 2510, 'καθάπτω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to seize upon\",\"long\":[\"to fit or fasten to, bind on\",\"to lay hold of, fasten on (hostilely)\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G0680\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθɑ.pto\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθɑ.ptow\",\"sbl\":\"kathaptō\",\"dic\":\"ka-THA-ptoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THA-ptoh\"},\"see\":[\"G0680\",\"G2596\"]}', 'fasten on'),
(2511, 2511, 'καθαρίζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to cleanse (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to make clean, cleanse\",[\"from physical stains and dirt\",[\"utensils, food\",\"a leper, to cleanse by curing\",\"to remove by cleansing\"],\"in a moral sense\",[\"to free from defilement of sin and from faults\",\"to purify from wickedness\",\"to free from guilt of sin, to purify\",\"to consecrate by cleansing or purifying\",\"to consecrate, dedicate\"]],\"to pronounce clean in a levitical sense\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2513\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θɑˈri.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θɑˈri.zow\",\"sbl\":\"katharizō\",\"dic\":\"ka-tha-REE-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-tha-REE-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2513\"]}', '(make) clean(-se), purge, purify'),
(2512, 2512, 'καθαρισμός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a washing off, i.e., (ceremonially) ablution, (morally) expiation\",\"long\":[\"a cleansing, purification, a ritual purgation or washing\",[\"of the washing of the Jews before and after their meals\",\"of levitical purification of women after childbirth\",\"a cleansing from the guilt of sins wrought by the expiatory sacrifice of Christ\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2511\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θɑ.riˈsmos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θɑ.riˈsmows\",\"sbl\":\"katharismos\",\"dic\":\"ka-tha-ree-SMOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-tha-ree-SMOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2511\"]}', 'cleansing, + purge, purification(-fying)'),
(2513, 2513, 'καθαρός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"clean (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"clean, pure\",[\"physically\",[\"purified by fire\",\"in a similitude, like a vine cleansed by pruning and so fitted to bear fruit\"],\"in a levitical sense\",[\"clean, the use of which is not forbidden, imparts no uncleanness\"],\"ethically\",[\"free from corrupt desire, from sin and guilt\",\"free from every admixture of what is false, sincere genuine\",\"blameless, innocent\",\"unstained with the guilt of anything\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θɑˈros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θɑˈrows\",\"sbl\":\"katharos\",\"dic\":\"ka-tha-ROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-tha-ROSE\"}}', 'clean, clear, pure'),
(2514, 2514, 'καθαρότης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"cleanness (ceremonially)\",\"long\":[\"cleanness, purity\",[\"in a Levitical sense\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2513\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θɑˈro.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θɑˈrow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"katharotēs\",\"dic\":\"ka-tha-ROH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-tha-ROH-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2513\"]}', 'purification'),
(2515, 2515, 'καθέδρα', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a bench (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"a chair, a seat\",[\"used of the exalted seat occupied by men of eminent rank or influence, as teachers and judges\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and the same as G1476\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθɛ.ðrɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθe̞.ðrɑ\",\"sbl\":\"kathedra\",\"dic\":\"ka-THEH-thra\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THAY-thra\"},\"see\":[\"G1476\",\"G2596\"]}', 'seat'),
(2516, 2516, 'καθέζομαι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to sit down\",\"long\":[\"to sit down, seat one\'s self, sit\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and the base of G1476\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθɛ.zo.mɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθe̞.zow.me\",\"sbl\":\"kathezomai\",\"dic\":\"ka-THEH-zoh-meh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THAY-zoh-may\"},\"see\":[\"G1476\",\"G2596\"]}', 'sit'),
(2517, 2517, 'καθεξῆς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"thereafter, i.e., consecutively; as a noun (by ellipsis of noun) a subsequent person or time\",\"long\":[\"one after another, successively, in order\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G1836\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θɛˈk͡ses\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θe̞ˈk͡se̞s\",\"sbl\":\"kathexēs\",\"dic\":\"ka-theh-KSASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-thay-KSASE\"},\"see\":[\"G1836\",\"G2596\"]}', 'after(-ward), by (in) order'),
(2518, 2518, 'καθεύδω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to lie down to rest, i.e., (by implication) to fall asleep (literally or figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"to fall asleep, drop off to sleep\",\"to sleep\",[\"to sleep normally\",\"euphemistically, to be dead\",\"metaphorically\",[\"to yield to sloth and sin\",\"to be indifferent to one\'s salvation\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and εὕδω (to sleep)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθɛβ.ðo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθev.ðow\",\"sbl\":\"katheudō\",\"dic\":\"ka-THEV-thoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THAVE-thoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\"]}', '(be a-)sleep'),
(2519, 2519, 'καθηγητής', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"a guide, i.e., (figuratively) a teacher\",\"long\":[\"a guide\",\"a master, teacher\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a compound of G2596 and G2233\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θe.ɣeˈtes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θe̞.ɣe̞ˈte̞s\",\"sbl\":\"kathēgētēs\",\"dic\":\"ka-thay-gay-TASE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-thay-gay-TASE\"},\"see\":[\"G2233\",\"G2596\"]}', 'master'),
(2520, 2520, 'καθήκω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to reach to, i.e., (neuter of present active participle, figuratively as adjective) becoming\",\"long\":[\"to come down\",\"to come to, reach to\",[\"it is becoming\",\"it is fit\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G2240\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθe.ko\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθe̞.kow\",\"sbl\":\"kathēkō\",\"dic\":\"ka-THAY-koh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THAY-koh\"},\"see\":[\"G2240\",\"G2596\"]}', 'convenient, fit'),
(2521, 2521, 'κάθημαι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and ἧμαι (to sit; akin to the base of G1476); to sit down; figuratively, to remain, reside\",\"long\":[\"to sit down, seat one\'s self\",\"to sit, be seated, of a place occupied\",[\"to have a fixed abode, to dwell\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈkɑ.θe.mɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈkɑ.θe̞.me\",\"sbl\":\"kathēmai\",\"dic\":\"KA-thay-meh\",\"dic_mod\":\"KA-thay-may\"},\"see\":[\"G1476\",\"G2596\"]}', 'dwell, sit (by, down)'),
(2522, 2522, 'καθημερινός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"quotidian\",\"long\":[\"daily\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G2250\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θe.mɛ.riˈnos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θe̞.me̞.riˈnows\",\"sbl\":\"kathēmerinos\",\"dic\":\"ka-thay-meh-ree-NOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-thay-may-ree-NOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2250\",\"G2596\"]}', 'daily'),
(2523, 2523, 'καθίζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to seat down, i.e., set (figuratively, appoint); intransitively, to sit (down); figuratively, to settle (hover, dwell)\",\"long\":[\"to make to sit down\",[\"to set, appoint, to confer a kingdom on one\"],\"intransitively\",[\"to sit down\",\"to sit\",[\"to have fixed one\'s abode\",\"to sojourn, to settle, settle down\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"another (active) form for G2516\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθi.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθi.zow\",\"sbl\":\"kathizō\",\"dic\":\"ka-THEE-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THEE-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2516\"]}', 'continue, set, sit (down), tarry'),
(2524, 2524, 'καθίημι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and ἵημι (to send); to lower\",\"long\":[\"to send down, to let down\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθi.e.mi\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθi.e̞.mi\",\"sbl\":\"kathiēmi\",\"dic\":\"ka-THEE-ay-mee\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THEE-ay-mee\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\"]}', 'let down'),
(2525, 2525, 'καθίστημι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to place down (permanently), i.e., (figuratively) to designate, constitute, convoy\",\"long\":[\"to set, place, put\",[\"to set one over a thing (in charge of it)\",\"to appoint one to administer an office\",\"to set down as, constitute, to declare, show to be\",\"to constitute, to render, make, cause to be\",\"to conduct or bring to a certain place\",\"to show or exhibit one\'s self\",[\"come forward as\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G2476\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθi.ste.mi\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθi.ste̞.mi\",\"sbl\":\"kathistēmi\",\"dic\":\"ka-THEE-stay-mee\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THEE-stay-mee\"},\"see\":[\"G2476\",\"G2596\"]}', 'appoint, be, conduct, make, ordain, set');
INSERT INTO `lexicon_greek` (`id`, `strongs`, `word`, `data`, `usage`) VALUES
(2526, 2526, 'καθό', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"according to which thing, i.e., precisely as, in proportion as\",\"long\":[\"according to what\",[\"as\",\"according as, in so far as, so far forth as\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G3739\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθow\",\"sbl\":\"katho\",\"dic\":\"ka-THOH\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THOH\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\",\"G3739\"]}', 'according to that, (inasmuch) as'),
(2527, 2527, 'καθόλου', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"on the whole, i.e., entirely\",\"long\":[\"wholly, entirely, at all\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G3650\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθo.lu\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθow.lu\",\"sbl\":\"katholou\",\"dic\":\"ka-THOH-loo\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THOH-loo\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\",\"G3650\"]}', 'at all'),
(2528, 2528, 'καθοπλίζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and G3695; to equip fully with armor\",\"long\":[\"furnish with arms\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θoˈpli.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θowˈpli.zow\",\"sbl\":\"kathoplizō\",\"dic\":\"ka-thoh-PLEE-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-thoh-PLEE-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\",\"G3695\"]}', 'arm'),
(2529, 2529, 'καθοράω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to behold fully, i.e., (figuratively) distinctly apprehend\",\"long\":[\"to look down, see from above, view from on high\",\"to see thoroughly, perceive clearly, understand\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G3708\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.θoˈrɑ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.θowˈrɑ.ow\",\"sbl\":\"kathoraō\",\"dic\":\"ka-thoh-RA-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-thoh-RA-oh\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\",\"G3708\"]}', 'clearly see'),
(2530, 2530, 'καθότι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and G3739 and G5100; according to which certain thing, i.e., as far (or inasmuch) as\",\"long\":[\"according to what\",[\"as far as, according as\",\"because that, because\",\"as just as\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθo.ti\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθow.ti\",\"sbl\":\"kathoti\",\"dic\":\"ka-THOH-tee\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THOH-tee\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\",\"G3739\",\"G5100\"]}', '(according, forasmuch) as, because (that)'),
(2531, 2531, 'καθώς', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"just (or inasmuch) as, that\",\"long\":[\"according as\",[\"just as, even as\",\"in proportion as, in the degree that\"],\"since, seeing that, agreeably to the fact that\",\"when, after that\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2596 and G5613\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈθos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈθows\",\"sbl\":\"kathōs\",\"dic\":\"ka-THOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-THOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G2596\",\"G5613\"]}', 'according to, (according, even) as, how, when'),
(2532, 2532, 'καί', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and, also, even, so then, too, etc.; often used in connection (or composition) with other particles or small words\",\"long\":[\"and, also, even, indeed, but\"]},\"deriv\":\"apparently, a primary particle, having a copulative and sometimes also a cumulative force\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ke\",\"sbl\":\"kai\",\"dic\":\"keh\",\"dic_mod\":\"kay\"}}', 'and, also, both, but, even, for, if, or, so, that, then, therefore, when, yet'),
(2533, 2533, 'Καϊάφας', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"as comely\",\"short\":\"the dell; Caiaphas (i.e., Cajepha), an Israelite\",\"long\":[\"a high priest of the Jews appointed to that office by Valerius Gratus, governor of Judaea, after removal of Simon, son of Camith, AD 18, and was removed AD 36 by Vitellius, governor of Syria, who appointed Jonathan, son of Ananus (Annus, father-in-law of Caiaphas), his successor\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Chaldee origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.iˈɑ.fɑs\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.iˈɑ.fɑs\",\"sbl\":\"kaiaphas\",\"dic\":\"ka-ee-AH-fahs\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-ee-AH-fahs\"}}', 'Caiaphas'),
(2534, 2534, 'καίγε', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and at least (or even, indeed)\",\"long\":[\"and at least, indeed\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2532 and G1065\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈkɛ.ɣɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈke.ʝe̞\",\"sbl\":\"kaige\",\"dic\":\"KEH-geh\",\"dic_mod\":\"KAY-gay\"},\"see\":[\"G1065\",\"G2532\"]}', 'and, at least'),
(2535, 2535, 'Κάϊν', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"maker, fabricator (literally smith)\",\"short\":\"Cain, (i.e., Cajin), the son of Adam\",\"long\":[\"the first born of Adam, and slew his brother, Abel\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H7014)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈkɑ.in\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈkɑ.in\",\"sbl\":\"kain\",\"dic\":\"KA-een\",\"dic_mod\":\"KA-een\"},\"see\":[\"H7014\"]}', 'Cain'),
(2536, 2536, 'Καϊνάν', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"their smith\",\"short\":\"Cainan (i.e., Kenan), the name of two patriarchs\",\"long\":[\"the son of Enos, Genesis 5:9\",\"son of Arphaxad and ancestor of Christ, Luke 3:36\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Hebrew origin (H7018)\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.iˈnɑn\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.iˈnɑn\",\"sbl\":\"kainan\",\"dic\":\"ka-ee-NAHN\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-ee-NAHN\"},\"see\":[\"H7018\"]}', 'Cainan'),
(2537, 2537, 'καινός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"new (especially in freshness; while G3501 is properly so with respect to age\",\"long\":[\"new\",[\"as respects form\",[\"recently made, fresh, recent, unused, unworn\"],\"as respects substance\",[\"of a new kind, unprecedented, novel, uncommon, unheard of\"]]]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɛˈnos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"keˈnows\",\"sbl\":\"kainos\",\"dic\":\"keh-NOSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"kay-NOSE\"},\"see\":[\"G3501\"]}', 'new'),
(2538, 2538, 'καινότης', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"renewal (figuratively)\",\"long\":[\"newness\",[\"in the new state of life in which the Holy Spirit places us so as to produce a new state which is eternal life\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2537\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɛˈno.tes\",\"ipa_mod\":\"keˈnow.te̞s\",\"sbl\":\"kainotēs\",\"dic\":\"keh-NOH-tase\",\"dic_mod\":\"kay-NOH-tase\"},\"see\":[\"G2537\"]}', 'newness'),
(2539, 2539, 'καίπερ', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and indeed, i.e., nevertheless or notwithstanding\",\"long\":[\"although\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2532 and G4007\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈkɛ.pɛr\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈke.pe̞r\",\"sbl\":\"kaiper\",\"dic\":\"KEH-per\",\"dic_mod\":\"KAY-pare\"},\"see\":[\"G2532\",\"G4007\"]}', 'and yet, although'),
(2540, 2540, 'καιρός', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"an occasion, i.e., set or proper time\",\"long\":[\"due measure\",\"a measure of time, a larger or smaller portion of time, hence:\",[\"a fixed and definite time, the time when things are brought to crisis, the decisive epoch waited for\",\"opportune or seasonable time\",\"the right time\",\"a limited period of time\",\"to what time brings, the state of the times, the things and events of time\"]]},\"deriv\":\"of uncertain affinity\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɛˈros\",\"ipa_mod\":\"keˈrows\",\"sbl\":\"kairos\",\"dic\":\"keh-ROSE\",\"dic_mod\":\"kay-ROSE\"},\"see\":[\"G5550\"],\"comment\":\"Compare G5550.\"}', 'X always, opportunity, (convenient, due) season, (due, short, while) time, a while'),
(2541, 2541, 'Καῖσαρ', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"severed\",\"short\":\"Caesar, a title of the Roman emperor\",\"long\":[\"the surname of Julius Caesar, which adopted by Octavius Augustus and his successors afterwards became a title, and was appropriated by the Roman emperors as part of their title\"]},\"deriv\":\"of Latin origin\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈkɛ.sɑr\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈke.sɑr\",\"sbl\":\"kaisar\",\"dic\":\"KEH-sahr\",\"dic_mod\":\"KAY-sahr\"}}', 'Caesar'),
(2542, 2542, 'Καισάρεια', '{\"def\":{\"lit\":\"severed\",\"short\":\"Caesaria, the name of two places in Palestine\",\"long\":[\"the city of Caesarea of Philippi, situated at the foot of Lebanon near the sources of the Jordan in Gaulanitis\",\"the city Caesarea of Palestine was built near the Mediterranean by Herod the Great on the site of Strabo\'s Tower, between Joppa and Dora\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2541\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɛˈsɑ.ri.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"keˈsɑ.ri.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"kaisareia\",\"dic\":\"keh-SA-ree-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"kay-SA-ree-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2541\"],\"comment\":\"Caesarea of Philippi was formerly called Paneas, but after being rebuilt by Philip the tetrarch, it was named Caesarea, in honor of Tiberias Caesar; subsequently called Neronias by Agrippa II, in honor of Nero. Caesarea of Palestine was provided with a magnificent harbor and had conferred upon it the name of Caesarea, in honor of Augustus. It was the residence of Roman procurators, and the majority of its inhabitants were Greeks.\"}', 'Caesarea'),
(2543, 2543, 'καίτοι', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and yet, i.e., nevertheless\",\"long\":[\"and yet, although\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2532 and G5104\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈkɛ.ty\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈke.ty\",\"sbl\":\"kaitoi\",\"dic\":\"KEH-too\",\"dic_mod\":\"KAY-too\"},\"see\":[\"G2532\",\"G5104\"]}', 'although'),
(2544, 2544, 'καίτοιγε', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"and yet indeed, i.e., although really\",\"long\":[\"and yet, thought\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2543 and G1065\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈkɛ.ty.ɣɛ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈke.ty.ʝe̞\",\"sbl\":\"kaitoige\",\"dic\":\"KEH-too-geh\",\"dic_mod\":\"KAY-too-gay\"},\"see\":[\"G1065\",\"G2543\"]}', 'nevertheless, though'),
(2545, 2545, 'καίω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to set on fire, i.e., kindle or (by implication) consume\",\"long\":[\"to set on fire, light, burning\",\"to burn, consume with fire\"]},\"deriv\":\"apparently a primary verb\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"ˈkɛ.o\",\"ipa_mod\":\"ˈke.ow\",\"sbl\":\"kaiō\",\"dic\":\"KEH-oh\",\"dic_mod\":\"KAY-oh\"}}', 'burn, light'),
(2546, 2546, 'κἀκεῖ', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"likewise in that place\",\"long\":[\"and there\",\"there also\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2532 and G1563\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈki\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈci\",\"sbl\":\"kakei\",\"dic\":\"ka-KEE\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-KEE\"},\"see\":[\"G1563\",\"G2532\"]}', 'and there, there (thither) also'),
(2547, 2547, 'κἀκεῖθεν', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"likewise from that place (or time)\",\"long\":[\"of place\",[\"and from thence, and thence\"],\"of time\",[\"and thereafter, and afterward\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G2532 and G1564\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈki.θɛn\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈci.θe̞n\",\"sbl\":\"kakeithen\",\"dic\":\"ka-KEE-then\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-KEE-thane\"},\"see\":[\"G1564\",\"G2532\"]}', 'and afterward (from) (thence), thence also'),
(2548, 2548, 'κἀκεῖνος', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"likewise that (or those)\",\"long\":[\"and he, he also\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2532 and G1565\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈki.nos\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈci.nows\",\"sbl\":\"kakeinos\",\"dic\":\"ka-KEE-nose\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-KEE-nose\"},\"see\":[\"G1565\",\"G2532\"]}', 'and him (other, them), even he, him also, them (also), (and) they'),
(2549, 2549, 'κακία', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"badness, i.e., (subjectively) depravity, or (actively) malignity, or (passively) trouble\",\"long\":[\"malignity, malice, ill-will, desire to injure\",\"wickedness, depravity\",[\"wickedness that is not ashamed to break laws\"],\"evil, trouble\"]},\"deriv\":\"from G2556\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑˈki.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑˈki.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"kakia\",\"dic\":\"ka-KEE-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-KEE-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2556\"]}', 'evil, malice(-iousness), naughtiness, wickedness'),
(2550, 2550, 'κακοήθεια', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"bad character, i.e., (specially) mischievousness\",\"long\":[\"bad character, depravity of heart and life\",\"malignant subtlety, malicious craftiness\"]},\"deriv\":\"from a compound of G2556 and G2239\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"kɑ.koˈe.θi.ɑ\",\"ipa_mod\":\"kɑ.kowˈe̞.θi.ɑ\",\"sbl\":\"kakoētheia\",\"dic\":\"ka-koh-A-thee-ah\",\"dic_mod\":\"ka-koh-A-thee-ah\"},\"see\":[\"G2239\",\"G2556\"]}', 'malignity'),
