(4879, 4980, 'σχολάζω', '{\"def\":{\"short\":\"to take a holiday, i.e., be at leisure for (by implication, devote oneself wholly to); figuratively, to be vacant (of a house)\",\"long\":[\"to cease from labor, to loiter\",\"to be free from labor, to be at leisure, to be idle\",[\"to have leisure for a thing\",\"to give one\'s self to a thing\"],\"of things\",[\"of places, to be unoccupied, empty\",\"of a centurion\'s vacant office\",\"of vacant ecclesiastical offices\",\"of officers without charge\"]]},\"deriv\":\"from G4981\",\"pronun\":{\"ipa\":\"sxoˈlɑ.zo\",\"ipa_mod\":\"sxowˈlɑ.zow\",\"sbl\":\"scholazō\",\"dic\":\"skoh-LA-zoh\",\"dic_mod\":\"skoh-LA-zoh\"},\"see\":[\"G4981\"]}', 'empty, give self'),
